  4. COMPLETE TODO LIST:

        - Command: `sudo apt-get install ant`
        - Verification: `ant -version` outputs installed version
     3. Install Git
        - Command: `sudo apt-get install git`
        - Verification: `git --version`
     4. Install CMake
        - Command: `sudo apt-get install cmake`
        - Verification: `cmake --version` (should be 3.22.1 or later)
     5. Install GCC or Clang
        - Command: `sudo apt-get install build-essential`
        - Verification: `gcc --version` (should be 11.x or newer)

        - Command: `git clone https://github.com/niklasso/minisat.git`
        - Build: Follow MiniSat’s README (usually `make`)
        - Verification: Run `minisat` executable and check for proper help message

        - Command: `git clone <SymMC-repo-url> /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC`
        - Verification: Repository folders (`Enhanced_Kodkod`, `Enumerator_Estimator`, `Datasets`) are present

        - Set `JAVA_HOME` to JDK 1.8 path
        - Export `PATH` to include Java and Ant binaries
        - Verification: `echo $JAVA_HOME` and `java -version`

        - Verification: Build completes without error, relevant JAR/class files produced
     10. Build Enumerator_Estimator
         - Command: `cd /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC/Enumerator_Estimator && ./build.sh`
         - Verification: `cmake-build-release` folder created, executable present

         - b) Test Enumerator_Estimator: `./cmake-build-release/minisat -getmcFSB ...` etc.
         - Verification: Outputs match expected results
     14. Test error handling

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  # 1. Install system dependencies: OpenJDK 8, Ant, CMake, GCC, Git, Python3 (optional), build-essential, wget, unzip
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        openjdk-8-jdk \
        ant \
        cmake \
        build-essential \
        git \
        python3 \
        wget \
        unzip \
        ca-certificates && \
      apt-get clean && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # 2. Set JAVA_HOME and update PATH for Java and Ant
  ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
  ENV PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:$PATH"
  # 3. Create user and working directories
  RUN useradd -ms /bin/bash cc
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  RUN chown -R cc:cc /home/cc
  USER cc
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 4. Clone SymMC repository (replace <SymMC-repo-url> with actual repo URL)
  # ARG SYMMC_REPO_URL
  # RUN git clone $SYMMC_REPO_URL /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # Instead, expect ADD/COPY of code at build time
  # 5. Clone and build MiniSat
  RUN git clone https://github.com/niklasso/minisat.git /home/cc/minisat && \
      cd /home/cc/minisat && \
      make -j$(nproc)
  # 6. Make MiniSat binary globally available
  ENV PATH="/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:${PATH}"
  # 7. Copy project files (expect context provides all source)
  COPY --chown=cc:cc . /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 8. (Optional) Export JAVA_HOME, update PATH in a profile script for interactive sessions
  RUN echo "export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=\$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile
  # 9. Prepare test directory if not present
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC/test
  # 10. Set default shell to bash and working directory
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 11. (Optional) Build Enhanced_Kodkod and Enumerator_Estimator on build, if desired
  # Uncomment if you want to build at image build time
  # RUN cd Enhanced_Kodkod && ./build.sh
  # RUN cd Enumerator_Estimator && ./build.sh
  # 12. Entrypoint: open shell by default
  ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 1 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  # 1. Install system dependencies: OpenJDK 8, Ant, CMake, GCC, Git, Python3 (optional), build-essential, wget, unzip
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        openjdk-8-jdk \
        ant \
        cmake \
        build-essential \
        git \
        python3 \
        wget \
        unzip \
        ca-certificates && \
      apt-get clean && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # 2. Set JAVA_HOME and update PATH for Java and Ant
  ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
  ENV PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:$PATH"
  # 3. Create user and working directories
  RUN useradd -ms /bin/bash cc
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  RUN chown -R cc:cc /home/cc
  USER cc
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 4. Clone SymMC repository (replace <SymMC-repo-url> with actual repo URL)
  # ARG SYMMC_REPO_URL
  # RUN git clone $SYMMC_REPO_URL /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # Instead, expect ADD/COPY of code at build time
  # 5. Clone and build MiniSat with troubleshooting output
  RUN git clone https://github.com/niklasso/minisat.git /home/cc/minisat && \
      cd /home/cc/minisat && \
      ls -l && \
      (cat README.md || true) && \
      make -j$(nproc) || (echo "MiniSat build failed. Directory listing:"; ls -l; echo "Makefile contents:"; cat Makefile || true; echo "README.md:"; cat README.md || true; exit 1)
  # 6. Make MiniSat binary globally available
  ENV PATH="/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:${PATH}"
  # 7. Copy project files (expect context provides all source)
  COPY --chown=cc:cc . /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 8. (Optional) Export JAVA_HOME, update PATH in a profile script for interactive sessions
  RUN echo "export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=\$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile
  # 9. Prepare test directory if not present
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC/test
  # 10. Set default shell to bash and working directory
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 11. (Optional) Build Enhanced_Kodkod and Enumerator_Estimator on build, if desired
  # Uncomment if you want to build at image build time
  # RUN cd Enhanced_Kodkod && ./build.sh
  # RUN cd Enumerator_Estimator && ./build.sh
  # 12. Entrypoint: open shell by default
  ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/bash"]

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  # 1. Install system dependencies: OpenJDK 8, Ant, CMake, GCC, Git, Python3 (optional), build-essential, wget, unzip
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        openjdk-8-jdk \
        ant \
        cmake \
        build-essential \
        git \
        python3 \
        wget \
        unzip \
        ca-certificates && \
      apt-get clean && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # 2. Set JAVA_HOME and update PATH for Java and Ant
  ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
  ENV PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:$PATH"
  # 3. Create user and working directories
  RUN useradd -ms /bin/bash cc
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  RUN chown -R cc:cc /home/cc
  USER cc
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 4. Clone SymMC repository (replace <SymMC-repo-url> with actual repo URL)
  # ARG SYMMC_REPO_URL
  # RUN git clone $SYMMC_REPO_URL /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # Instead, expect ADD/COPY of code at build time
  # 5. Clone and build MiniSat with troubleshooting and extra diagnostics
  RUN git clone https://github.com/niklasso/minisat.git /home/cc/minisat && \
      cd /home/cc/minisat && \
      git submodule update --init --recursive || true && \
      ls -l && \
      (cat README.md || true) && \
      make clean || true && \
      make -j$(nproc) > minisat_build.log 2>&1 || ( \
          echo "MiniSat build failed. Directory listing:"; ls -l; \
          echo "Makefile contents:"; cat Makefile || true; \
          echo "README.md:"; cat README.md || true; \
          echo "minisat_build.log:"; cat minisat_build.log || true; \
          exit 1)
  # 6. Make MiniSat binary globally available (handle alternative output path)
  RUN if [ -f /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      elif [ -f /home/cc/minisat/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      fi
  ENV PATH="/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:${PATH}"
  # 7. Copy project files (expect context provides all source)
  COPY --chown=cc:cc . /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 8. (Optional) Export JAVA_HOME, update PATH in a profile script for interactive sessions
  RUN echo "export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=\$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile
  # 9. Prepare test directory if not present
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC/test
  # 10. Set default shell to bash and working directory
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 11. Build Enhanced_Kodkod and Enumerator_Estimator on build
  RUN cd Enhanced_Kodkod && ./build.sh
  RUN cd Enumerator_Estimator && ./build.sh
  # 12. Entrypoint: open shell by default
  ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 3 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  # 1. Install system dependencies: OpenJDK 8, Ant, CMake, GCC, Git, Python3 (optional), build-essential, wget, unzip, libz-dev
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        openjdk-8-jdk \
        ant \
        cmake \
        build-essential \
        git \
        python3 \
        wget \
        unzip \
        ca-certificates \
        libz-dev && \
      apt-get clean && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # 2. Set JAVA_HOME and update PATH for Java and Ant
  ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
  ENV PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:$PATH"
  # 3. Create user and working directories
  RUN useradd -ms /bin/bash cc
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  RUN chown -R cc:cc /home/cc
  USER cc
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 4. Clone SymMC repository (replace <SymMC-repo-url> with actual repo URL)
  # ARG SYMMC_REPO_URL
  # RUN git clone $SYMMC_REPO_URL /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # Instead, expect ADD/COPY of code at build time
  # 5. Clone and build MiniSat with troubleshooting and extra diagnostics.
  # Show last 50 lines of minisat_build.log if build fails.
  RUN git clone https://github.com/niklasso/minisat.git /home/cc/minisat && \
      cd /home/cc/minisat && \
      git submodule update --init --recursive || true && \
      ls -l && \
      (cat README.md || true) && \
      make clean || true && \
      make -j$(nproc) > minisat_build.log 2>&1 || ( \
          echo "MiniSat build failed. Directory listing:"; ls -l; \
          echo "Makefile contents:"; cat Makefile || true; \
          echo "README.md:"; cat README.md || true; \
          echo "Last 50 lines of minisat_build.log:"; tail -n 50 minisat_build.log || true; \
          exit 1)
  # 6. Make MiniSat binary globally available (handle alternative output path)
  RUN if [ -f /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      elif [ -f /home/cc/minisat/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      fi
  ENV PATH="/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:${PATH}"
  # 7. Copy project files (expect context provides all source)
  COPY --chown=cc:cc . /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 8. (Optional) Export JAVA_HOME, update PATH in a profile script for interactive sessions
  RUN echo "export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=\$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile
  # 9. Prepare test directory if not present
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC/test
  # 10. Set default shell to bash and working directory
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 11. Build Enhanced_Kodkod and Enumerator_Estimator on build
  RUN cd Enhanced_Kodkod && ./build.sh
  RUN cd Enumerator_Estimator && ./build.sh
  # 12. Entrypoint: open shell by default
  ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 4 ---

  #11 1.076 
  #11 1.076 SRCS = $(wildcard minisat/core/*.cc) $(wildcard minisat/simp/*.cc) $(wildcard minisat/utils/*.cc)
  #11 1.076 HDRS = $(wildcard minisat/mtl/*.h) $(wildcard minisat/core/*.h) $(wildcard minisat/simp/*.h) $(wildcard minisat/utils/*.h)
  #11 1.076 OBJS = $(filter-out %Main.o, $(SRCS:.cc=.o))
  #11 1.076

  #11 1.076 d:	$(BUILD_DIR)/debug/bin/$(MINISAT)
  #11 1.076 p:	$(BUILD_DIR)/profile/bin/$(MINISAT)
  #11 1.076 sh:	$(BUILD_DIR)/dynamic/bin/$(MINISAT)

  #11 1.076 cd:	$(BUILD_DIR)/debug/bin/$(MINISAT_CORE)
  #11 1.076 cp:	$(BUILD_DIR)/profile/bin/$(MINISAT_CORE)
  #11 1.076 csh:	$(BUILD_DIR)/dynamic/bin/$(MINISAT_CORE)
  #11 1.076 
  #11 1.076 lr:	$(BUILD_DIR)/release/lib/$(MINISAT_SLIB)
  #11 1.076 ld:	$(BUILD_DIR)/debug/lib/$(MINISAT_SLIB)
  #11 1.076 lp:	$(BUILD_DIR)/profile/lib/$(MINISAT_SLIB)
  #11 1.076 lsh:	$(BUILD_DIR)/dynamic/lib/$(MINISAT_DLIB).$(SOMAJOR).$(SOMINOR)$(SORELEASE)
  #11 1.076 
  #11 1.076 ## Build-type Compile-flags:
  #11 1.076 $(BUILD_DIR)/release/%.o:			MINISAT_CXXFLAGS +=$(MINISAT_REL) $(MINISAT_RELSYM)
  #11 1.076 $(BUILD_DIR)/debug/%.o:				MINISAT_CXXFLAGS +=$(MINISAT_DEB) -g
  #11 1.076 $(BUILD_DIR)/profile/%.o:			MINISAT_CXXFLAGS +=$(MINISAT_PRF) -pg
  #11 1.076 $(BUILD_DIR)/dynamic/%.o:			MINISAT_CXXFLAGS +=$(MINISAT_REL) $(MINISAT_FPIC)
  #11 1.076 
  #11 1.076 ## Build-type Link-flags:
  #11 1.076 $(BUILD_DIR)/profile/bin/$(MINISAT):		MINISAT_LDFLAGS += -pg
  #11 1.076 $(BUILD_DIR)/release/bin/$(MINISAT):		MINISAT_LDFLAGS += --static $(MINISAT_RELSYM)
  #11 1.076 $(BUILD_DIR)/profile/bin/$(MINISAT_CORE):	MINISAT_LDFLAGS += -pg
  #11 1.076 $(BUILD_DIR)/release/bin/$(MINISAT_CORE):	MINISAT_LDFLAGS += --static $(MINISAT_RELSYM)
  #11 1.076 
  #11 1.076 ## Executable dependencies
  #11 1.076 $(BUILD_DIR)/release/bin/$(MINISAT):	 	$(BUILD_DIR)/release/minisat/simp/Main.o $(BUILD_DIR)/release/lib/$(MINISAT_SLIB)
  #11 1.076 $(BUILD_DIR)/debug/bin/$(MINISAT):	 	$(BUILD_DIR)/debug/minisat/simp/Main.o $(BUILD_DIR)/debug/lib/$(MINISAT_SLIB)
  #11 1.076 $(BUILD_DIR)/profile/bin/$(MINISAT):	 	$(BUILD_DIR)/profile/minisat/simp/Main.o $(BUILD_DIR)/profile/lib/$(MINISAT_SLIB)
  #11 1.076 # need the main-file be compiled with fpic?
  #11 1.076 $(BUILD_DIR)/dynamic/bin/$(MINISAT):	 	$(BUILD_DIR)/dynamic/minisat/simp/Main.o $(BUILD_DIR)/dynamic/lib/$(MINISAT_DLIB)
  #11 1.076 
  #11 1.076 ## Executable dependencies (core-version)

  #11 1.076 $(BUILD_DIR)/debug/bin/$(MINISAT_CORE):	 	$(BUILD_DIR)/debug/minisat/core/Main.o $(BUILD_DIR)/debug/lib/$(MINISAT_SLIB)

  #11 1.076 ## Library dependencies

  #11 1.076 $(BUILD_DIR)/debug/lib/$(MINISAT_SLIB):		$(foreach o,$(OBJS),$(BUILD_DIR)/debug/$(o))
  #11 1.076 $(BUILD_DIR)/profile/lib/$(MINISAT_SLIB):	$(foreach o,$(OBJS),$(BUILD_DIR)/profile/$(o))

  #11 1.076 
  #11 1.076 ## Compile rules (these should be unified, buit I have not yet found a way which works in GNU Make)
  #11 1.076 $(BUILD_DIR)/release/%.o:	%.cc
  #11 1.076 	$(ECHO) Compiling: $@
  #11 1.076 	$(VERB) mkdir -p $(dir $@)
  #11 1.076 	$(VERB) $(CXX) $(MINISAT_CXXFLAGS) $(CXXFLAGS) -c -o $@ $< -MMD -MF $(BUILD_DIR)/release/$*.d
  #11 1.076 
  #11 1.076 $(BUILD_DIR)/profile/%.o:	%.cc
  #11 1.076 	$(ECHO) Compiling: $@
  #11 1.076 	$(VERB) mkdir -p $(dir $@)
  #11 1.076 	$(VERB) $(CXX) $(MINISAT_CXXFLAGS) $(CXXFLAGS) -c -o $@ $< -MMD -MF $(BUILD_DIR)/profile/$*.d
  #11 1.076 
  #11 1.076 $(BUILD_DIR)/debug/%.o:	%.cc
  #11 1.076 	$(ECHO) Compiling: $@
  #11 1.076 	$(VERB) mkdir -p $(dir $@)
  #11 1.076 	$(VERB) $(CXX) $(MINISAT_CXXFLAGS) $(CXXFLAGS) -c -o $@ $< -MMD -MF $(BUILD_DIR)/debug/$*.d
  #11 1.076 
  #11 1.076 $(BUILD_DIR)/dynamic/%.o:	%.cc
  #11 1.076 	$(ECHO) Compiling: $@
  #11 1.076 	$(VERB) mkdir -p $(dir $@)
  #11 1.076 	$(VERB) $(CXX) $(MINISAT_CXXFLAGS) $(CXXFLAGS) -c -o $@ $< -MMD -MF $(BUILD_DIR)/dynamic/$*.d
  #11 1.076 
  #11 1.076 ## Linking rule
  #11 1.076 $(BUILD_DIR)/release/bin/$(MINISAT) $(BUILD_DIR)/debug/bin/$(MINISAT) $(BUILD_DIR)/profile/bin/$(MINISAT) $(BUILD_DIR)/dynamic/bin/$(MINISAT)\
  #11 1.076 $(BUILD_DIR)/release/bin/$(MINISAT_CORE) $(BUILD_DIR)/debug/bin/$(MINISAT_CORE) $(BUILD_DIR)/profile/bin/$(MINISAT_CORE) $(BUILD_DIR)/dynamic/bin/$(MINISAT_CORE):
  #11 1.076 	$(ECHO) Linking Binary: $@
  #11 1.076 	$(VERB) mkdir -p $(dir $@)
  #11 1.076 	$(VERB) $(CXX) $^ $(MINISAT_LDFLAGS) $(LDFLAGS) -o $@
  #11 1.076 
  #11 1.076 ## Static Library rule
  #11 1.076 %/lib/$(MINISAT_SLIB):
  #11 1.076 	$(ECHO) Linking Static Library: $@
  #11 1.076 	$(VERB) mkdir -p $(dir $@)
  #11 1.076 	$(VERB) $(AR) -rcs $@ $^
  #11 1.076 
  #11 1.076 ## Shared Library rule
  #11 1.076 $(BUILD_DIR)/dynamic/lib/$(MINISAT_DLIB).$(SOMAJOR).$(SOMINOR)$(SORELEASE)\
  #11 1.076  $(BUILD_DIR)/dynamic/lib/$(MINISAT_DLIB).$(SOMAJOR)\
  #11 1.076  $(BUILD_DIR)/dynamic/lib/$(MINISAT_DLIB):
  #11 1.076 	$(ECHO) Linking Shared Library: $@
  #11 1.076 	$(VERB) mkdir -p $(dir $@)
  #11 1.076 	$(VERB) $(CXX) $(MINISAT_LDFLAGS) $(LDFLAGS) -o $@ -shared -Wl,-soname,$(MINISAT_DLIB).$(SOMAJOR) $^
  #11 1.076 	$(VERB) ln -sf $(MINISAT_DLIB).$(SOMAJOR).$(SOMINOR)$(SORELEASE) $(BUILD_DIR)/dynamic/lib/$(MINISAT_DLIB).$(SOMAJOR)
  #11 1.076 	$(VERB) ln -sf $(MINISAT_DLIB).$(SOMAJOR) $(BUILD_DIR)/dynamic/lib/$(MINISAT_DLIB)
  #11 1.076 
  #11 1.076 install:	install-headers install-lib install-bin
  #11 1.076 install-debug:	install-headers install-lib-debug
  #11 1.076 
  #11 1.076 install-headers:
  #11 1.076 #       Create directories
  #11 1.076 	$(INSTALL) -d $(DESTDIR)$(includedir)/minisat
  #11 1.076 	for dir in mtl utils core simp; do \
  #11 1.076 	  $(INSTALL) -d $(DESTDIR)$(includedir)/minisat/$$dir ; \
  #11 1.076 	done
  #11 1.076 #       Install headers
  #11 1.076 	for h in $(HDRS) ; do \
  #11 1.076 	  $(INSTALL) -m 644 $$h $(DESTDIR)$(includedir)/$$h ; \
  #11 1.076 	done
  #11 1.076 
  #11 1.076 install-lib-debug: $(BUILD_DIR)/debug/lib/$(MINISAT_SLIB)

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  # 1. Install system dependencies: OpenJDK 8, Ant, CMake, GCC, Git, Python3 (optional), build-essential, wget, unzip, libz-dev
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        openjdk-8-jdk \
        ant \
        cmake \
        build-essential \
        git \
        python3 \
        wget \
        unzip \
        ca-certificates \
        libz-dev \
        g++ \
        make && \
      apt-get clean && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # 2. Set JAVA_HOME and update PATH for Java and Ant
  ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
  ENV PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:$PATH"
  # 3. Create user and working directories
  RUN useradd -ms /bin/bash cc
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  RUN chown -R cc:cc /home/cc
  USER cc
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 4. Clone SymMC repository (replace <SymMC-repo-url> with actual repo URL)
  # ARG SYMMC_REPO_URL
  # RUN git clone $SYMMC_REPO_URL /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # Instead, expect ADD/COPY of code at build time
  # 5. Clone and build MiniSat with diagnostics and build log output for debugging.
  RUN git clone https://github.com/niklasso/minisat.git /home/cc/minisat && \
      cd /home/cc/minisat && \
      git submodule update --init --recursive || true && \
      ls -l && \
      (cat README.md || true) && \
      make clean || true && \
      make -j$(nproc) > minisat_build.log 2>&1 || ( \
          echo "MiniSat build failed. Directory listing:"; ls -l; \
          echo "Makefile contents:"; cat Makefile || true; \
          echo "README.md:"; cat README.md || true; \
          echo "Last 50 lines of minisat_build.log:"; tail -n 50 minisat_build.log || true; \
          cat minisat_build.log || true; \
          exit 1) && \
      cat minisat_build.log || true
  # 6. Make MiniSat binary globally available (handle alternative output path)
  RUN if [ -f /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      elif [ -f /home/cc/minisat/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      fi
  ENV PATH="/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:${PATH}"
  # 7. Copy project files (expect context provides all source)
  COPY --chown=cc:cc . /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 8. (Optional) Export JAVA_HOME, update PATH in a profile script for interactive sessions
  RUN echo "export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=\$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile
  # 9. Prepare test directory if not present
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC/test
  # 10. Set default shell to bash and working directory
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 11. Build Enhanced_Kodkod and Enumerator_Estimator on build
  RUN cd Enhanced_Kodkod && ./build.sh
  RUN cd Enumerator_Estimator && ./build.sh
  # 12. Entrypoint: open shell by default
  ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 5 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  # 1. Install system dependencies: OpenJDK 8, Ant, CMake, GCC, Git, Python3 (optional), build-essential, wget, unzip, libz-dev
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        openjdk-8-jdk \
        ant \
        cmake \
        build-essential \
        git \
        python3 \
        wget \
        unzip \
        ca-certificates \
        libz-dev \
        g++ \
        make && \
      apt-get clean && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # 2. Set JAVA_HOME and update PATH for Java and Ant
  ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
  ENV PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:$PATH"
  # 3. Create user and working directories
  RUN useradd -ms /bin/bash cc
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  RUN chown -R cc:cc /home/cc
  USER cc
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 4. Clone SymMC repository (replace <SymMC-repo-url> with actual repo URL)
  # ARG SYMMC_REPO_URL
  # RUN git clone $SYMMC_REPO_URL /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # Instead, expect ADD/COPY of code at build time
  # 5. Clone and build MiniSat with diagnostics and build log output for debugging.
  RUN git clone https://github.com/niklasso/minisat.git /home/cc/minisat && \
      cd /home/cc/minisat && \
      git submodule update --init --recursive || true && \
      ls -l && \
      (cat README.md || true) && \
      make clean || true && \
      make -j$(nproc) > minisat_build.log 2>&1 || ( \
          echo "MiniSat build failed. Directory listing:"; ls -l; \
          echo "Makefile contents:"; cat Makefile || true; \
          echo "README.md:"; cat README.md || true; \
          echo "Last 50 lines of minisat_build.log:"; tail -n 50 minisat_build.log || true; \
          cat minisat_build.log || true; \
          exit 1) && \
      cat minisat_build.log || true
  # 6. Make MiniSat binary globally available (handle alternative output path)
  RUN if [ -f /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      elif [ -f /home/cc/minisat/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      fi
  ENV PATH="/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:${PATH}"
  # 7. Copy project files (expect context provides all source)
  COPY --chown=cc:cc . /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 8. (Optional) Export JAVA_HOME, update PATH in a profile script for interactive sessions
  RUN echo "export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=\$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile
  # 9. Prepare test directory if not present
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC/test
  # 10. Set default shell to bash and working directory
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 11. Diagnostics before Enhanced_Kodkod build
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing for Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && \
      ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== build.sh contents ===" && \
      cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh || true && \
      chmod +x Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh
  # 11b. Build Enhanced_Kodkod and Enumerator_Estimator on build
  RUN cd Enhanced_Kodkod && ./build.sh
  RUN cd Enumerator_Estimator && ./build.sh
  # 12. Entrypoint: open shell by default
  ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/bash"]

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  # 1. Install system dependencies: OpenJDK 8, Ant, CMake, GCC, Git, Python3 (optional), build-essential, wget, unzip, libz-dev
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        openjdk-8-jdk \
        ant \
        cmake \
        build-essential \
        git \
        python3 \
        wget \
        unzip \
        ca-certificates \
        libz-dev \
        g++ \
        make && \
      apt-get clean && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # 2. Set JAVA_HOME and update PATH for Java and Ant
  ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
  ENV PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:$PATH"
  # 3. Create user and working directories
  RUN useradd -ms /bin/bash cc
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  RUN chown -R cc:cc /home/cc
  USER cc
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 4. Clone SymMC repository (replace <SymMC-repo-url> with actual repo URL)
  # ARG SYMMC_REPO_URL
  # RUN git clone $SYMMC_REPO_URL /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # Instead, expect ADD/COPY of code at build time
  # 5. Clone and build MiniSat with diagnostics and build log output for debugging.
  RUN git clone https://github.com/niklasso/minisat.git /home/cc/minisat && \
      cd /home/cc/minisat && \
      git submodule update --init --recursive || true && \
      ls -l && \
      (cat README.md || true) && \
      make clean || true && \
      make -j$(nproc) > minisat_build.log 2>&1 || ( \
          echo "MiniSat build failed. Directory listing:"; ls -l; \
          echo "Makefile contents:"; cat Makefile || true; \
          echo "README.md:"; cat README.md || true; \
          echo "Last 50 lines of minisat_build.log:"; tail -n 50 minisat_build.log || true; \
          cat minisat_build.log || true; \
          exit 1) && \
      cat minisat_build.log || true
  # 6. Make MiniSat binary globally available (handle alternative output path)
  RUN if [ -f /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      elif [ -f /home/cc/minisat/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      fi
  ENV PATH="/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:${PATH}"
  # 7. Copy project files (expect context provides all source)
  COPY --chown=cc:cc . /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 8. (Optional) Export JAVA_HOME, update PATH in a profile script for interactive sessions
  RUN echo "export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=\$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile
  # 9. Prepare test directory if not present
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC/test
  # 10. Set default shell to bash and working directory
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 11. Diagnostics before Enhanced_Kodkod build
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing for Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && \
      ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== build.sh contents ===" && \
      cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh || true && \
      chmod +x Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh
  # 11a. Output directory listing and contents before build for further debugging
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing inside Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/src ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/src || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/lib ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/lib || true
  # 11b. Build Enhanced_Kodkod with error output on failure
  RUN cd Enhanced_Kodkod && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1 || ( \
        echo '=== Enhanced_Kodkod build failed! ==='; \
        echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
        tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
        cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
        exit 1)
  # 11c. Show build log for review even if build succeeds
  RUN cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build_sh_output.log || true
  # 12. Build Enumerator_Estimator (keep after Enhanced_Kodkod success)
  RUN cd Enumerator_Estimator && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1 || ( \
        echo '=== Enumerator_Estimator build failed! ==='; \
        echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
        tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
        cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
        exit 1)
  RUN cat Enumerator_Estimator/build_sh_output.log || true
  # 13. Entrypoint: open shell by default
  ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 7 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  # 1. Install system dependencies: OpenJDK 8, Ant, CMake, GCC, Git, Python3 (optional), build-essential, wget, unzip, libz-dev
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        openjdk-8-jdk \
        ant \
        cmake \
        build-essential \
        git \
        python3 \
        wget \
        unzip \
        ca-certificates \
        libz-dev \
        g++ \
        make && \
      apt-get clean && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # 2. Set JAVA_HOME and update PATH for Java and Ant
  ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
  ENV PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:$PATH"
  # 3. Create user and working directories
  RUN useradd -ms /bin/bash cc
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  RUN chown -R cc:cc /home/cc
  USER cc
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 4. Clone SymMC repository (replace <SymMC-repo-url> with actual repo URL)
  # ARG SYMMC_REPO_URL
  # RUN git clone $SYMMC_REPO_URL /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # Instead, expect ADD/COPY of code at build time
  # 5. Clone and build MiniSat with diagnostics and build log output for debugging.
  RUN git clone https://github.com/niklasso/minisat.git /home/cc/minisat && \
      cd /home/cc/minisat && \
      git submodule update --init --recursive || true && \
      ls -l && \
      (cat README.md || true) && \
      make clean || true && \
      make -j$(nproc) > minisat_build.log 2>&1 || ( \
          echo "MiniSat build failed. Directory listing:"; ls -l; \
          echo "Makefile contents:"; cat Makefile || true; \
          echo "README.md:"; cat README.md || true; \
          echo "Last 50 lines of minisat_build.log:"; tail -n 50 minisat_build.log || true; \
          cat minisat_build.log || true; \
          exit 1) && \
      cat minisat_build.log || true
  # 6. Make MiniSat binary globally available (handle alternative output path)
  RUN if [ -f /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      elif [ -f /home/cc/minisat/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      fi
  ENV PATH="/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:${PATH}"
  # 7. Copy project files (expect context provides all source)
  COPY --chown=cc:cc . /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 8. (Optional) Export JAVA_HOME, update PATH in a profile script for interactive sessions
  RUN echo "export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=\$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile
  # 9. Prepare test directory if not present
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC/test
  # 10. Set default shell to bash and working directory
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 11. Diagnostics before Enhanced_Kodkod build
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing for Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && \
      ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== build.sh contents ===" && \
      cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh || true && \
      chmod +x Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh
  # 11a. Output directory listing and contents before build for further debugging
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing inside Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/src ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/src || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/lib ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/lib || true
  # 11b. Attempt to build Enhanced_Kodkod, always output build log for debugging
  RUN cd Enhanced_Kodkod && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1; \
      status=$?; \
      echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
      tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
      cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
      if [ $status -ne 0 ]; then \
        echo '=== Enhanced_Kodkod build failed! ==='; \
        exit $status; \
      fi
  # 12. Build Enumerator_Estimator (keep after Enhanced_Kodkod success)
  RUN cd Enumerator_Estimator && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1 || ( \
        echo '=== Enumerator_Estimator build failed! ==='; \
        echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
        tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
        cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
        exit 1)
  RUN cat Enumerator_Estimator/build_sh_output.log || true
  # 13. Entrypoint: open shell by default
  ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 8 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  # 1. Install system dependencies: OpenJDK 8, Ant, CMake, GCC, Git, Python3 (optional), build-essential, wget, unzip, libz-dev
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        openjdk-8-jdk \
        ant \
        cmake \
        build-essential \
        git \
        python3 \
        wget \
        unzip \
        ca-certificates \
        libz-dev \
        g++ \
        make && \
      apt-get clean && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # 2. Set JAVA_HOME and update PATH for Java and Ant
  ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
  ENV PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:$PATH"
  # 3. Create user and working directories
  RUN useradd -ms /bin/bash cc
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  RUN chown -R cc:cc /home/cc
  USER cc
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 4. Clone SymMC repository (replace <SymMC-repo-url> with actual repo URL)
  # ARG SYMMC_REPO_URL
  # RUN git clone $SYMMC_REPO_URL /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # Instead, expect ADD/COPY of code at build time
  # 5. Clone and build MiniSat with diagnostics and build log output for debugging.
  RUN git clone https://github.com/niklasso/minisat.git /home/cc/minisat && \
      cd /home/cc/minisat && \
      git submodule update --init --recursive || true && \
      ls -l && \
      (cat README.md || true) && \
      make clean || true && \
      make -j$(nproc) > minisat_build.log 2>&1 || ( \
          echo "MiniSat build failed. Directory listing:"; ls -l; \
          echo "Makefile contents:"; cat Makefile || true; \
          echo "README.md:"; cat README.md || true; \
          echo "Last 50 lines of minisat_build.log:"; tail -n 50 minisat_build.log || true; \
          cat minisat_build.log || true; \
          exit 1) && \
      cat minisat_build.log || true
  # 6. Make MiniSat binary globally available (handle alternative output path)
  RUN if [ -f /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      elif [ -f /home/cc/minisat/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      fi
  ENV PATH="/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:${PATH}"
  # 7. Copy project files (expect context provides all source)
  COPY --chown=cc:cc . /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 8. (Optional) Export JAVA_HOME, update PATH in a profile script for interactive sessions
  RUN echo "export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=\$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile
  # 9. Prepare test directory if not present
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC/test
  # 10. Set default shell to bash and working directory
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 11. Diagnostics before Enhanced_Kodkod build
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing for Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && \
      ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== build.sh contents ===" && \
      cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh || true && \
      chmod +x Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh
  # 11a. Output directory listing and contents before build for further debugging
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing inside Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/src ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/src || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/lib ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/lib || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/util ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/util || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ===" && (cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml || true)
  # 11b. Check for required files before build, then attempt to build Enhanced_Kodkod, always output build log for debugging
  RUN if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh ]; then \
        echo "build.sh missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ]; then \
        echo "build.xml missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -d Enhanced_Kodkod/src ]; then \
        echo "src directory missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      cd Enhanced_Kodkod && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1; \
      status=$?; \
      echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
      tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
      cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
      if [ $status -ne 0 ]; then \
        echo '=== Enhanced_Kodkod build failed! ==='; \
        exit $status; \
      fi
  # 12. Build Enumerator_Estimator (keep after Enhanced_Kodkod success)
  RUN cd Enumerator_Estimator && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1 || ( \
        echo '=== Enumerator_Estimator build failed! ==='; \
        echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
        tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
        cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
        exit 1)
  RUN cat Enumerator_Estimator/build_sh_output.log || true
  # 13. Entrypoint: open shell by default
  ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 9 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  # 1. Install system dependencies: OpenJDK 8, Ant, CMake, GCC, Git, Python3 (optional), build-essential, wget, unzip, libz-dev
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        openjdk-8-jdk \
        ant \
        cmake \
        build-essential \
        git \
        python3 \
        wget \
        unzip \
        ca-certificates \
        libz-dev \
        g++ \
        make && \
      apt-get clean && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # 2. Set JAVA_HOME and update PATH for Java and Ant
  ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
  ENV PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:$PATH"
  # 3. Create user and working directories
  RUN useradd -ms /bin/bash cc
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  RUN chown -R cc:cc /home/cc
  USER cc
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 4. Clone SymMC repository (replace <SymMC-repo-url> with actual repo URL)
  # ARG SYMMC_REPO_URL
  # RUN git clone $SYMMC_REPO_URL /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # Instead, expect ADD/COPY of code at build time
  # 5. Clone and build MiniSat with diagnostics and build log output for debugging.
  RUN git clone https://github.com/niklasso/minisat.git /home/cc/minisat && \
      cd /home/cc/minisat && \
      git submodule update --init --recursive || true && \
      ls -l && \
      (cat README.md || true) && \
      make clean || true && \
      make -j$(nproc) > minisat_build.log 2>&1 || ( \
          echo "MiniSat build failed. Directory listing:"; ls -l; \
          echo "Makefile contents:"; cat Makefile || true; \
          echo "README.md:"; cat README.md || true; \
          echo "Last 50 lines of minisat_build.log:"; tail -n 50 minisat_build.log || true; \
          cat minisat_build.log || true; \
          exit 1) && \
      cat minisat_build.log || true
  # 6. Make MiniSat binary globally available (handle alternative output path)
  RUN if [ -f /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      elif [ -f /home/cc/minisat/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      fi
  ENV PATH="/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:${PATH}"
  # 7. Copy project files (expect context provides all source)
  COPY --chown=cc:cc . /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 8. (Optional) Export JAVA_HOME, update PATH in a profile script for interactive sessions
  RUN echo "export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=\$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile
  # 9. Prepare test directory if not present
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC/test
  # 10. Set default shell to bash and working directory
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 11. Diagnostics before Enhanced_Kodkod build
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing for Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && \
      ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== build.sh contents ===" && \
      cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh || true && \
      chmod +x Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh
  # 11a. Output directory listing and contents before build for further debugging
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing inside Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/src ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/src || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/lib ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/lib || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/util ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/util || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ===" && (cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml || true)
  # 11b. Check for required files before build, then attempt to build Enhanced_Kodkod, always output build log for debugging
  RUN if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh ]; then \
        echo "build.sh missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ]; then \
        echo "build.xml missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -d Enhanced_Kodkod/src ]; then \
        echo "src directory missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      cd Enhanced_Kodkod && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1; \
      status=$?; \
      echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
      tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
      cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
      if [ $status -ne 0 ]; then \
        echo '=== Enhanced_Kodkod build failed! ==='; \
        exit $status; \
      fi
  # 12. Build Enumerator_Estimator (keep after Enhanced_Kodkod success)
  RUN cd Enumerator_Estimator && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1 || ( \
        echo '=== Enumerator_Estimator build failed! ==='; \
        echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
        tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
        cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
        exit 1)
  RUN cat Enumerator_Estimator/build_sh_output.log || true
  # 13. Entrypoint: open shell by default
  ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 10 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  # 1. Install system dependencies: OpenJDK 8, Ant, CMake, GCC, Git, Python3 (optional), build-essential, wget, unzip, libz-dev
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        openjdk-8-jdk \
        ant \
        cmake \
        build-essential \
        git \
        python3 \
        wget \
        unzip \
        ca-certificates \
        libz-dev \
        g++ \
        make && \
      apt-get clean && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # 2. Set JAVA_HOME and update PATH for Java and Ant
  ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
  ENV PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:$PATH"
  # 3. Create user and working directories
  RUN useradd -ms /bin/bash cc
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  RUN chown -R cc:cc /home/cc
  USER cc
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 4. Clone SymMC repository (replace <SymMC-repo-url> with actual repo URL)
  # ARG SYMMC_REPO_URL
  # RUN git clone $SYMMC_REPO_URL /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # Instead, expect ADD/COPY of code at build time
  # 5. Clone and build MiniSat with diagnostics and build log output for debugging.
  RUN git clone https://github.com/niklasso/minisat.git /home/cc/minisat && \
      cd /home/cc/minisat && \
      git submodule update --init --recursive || true && \
      ls -l && \
      (cat README.md || true) && \
      make clean || true && \
      make -j$(nproc) > minisat_build.log 2>&1 || ( \
          echo "MiniSat build failed. Directory listing:"; ls -l; \
          echo "Makefile contents:"; cat Makefile || true; \
          echo "README.md:"; cat README.md || true; \
          echo "Last 50 lines of minisat_build.log:"; tail -n 50 minisat_build.log || true; \
          cat minisat_build.log || true; \
          exit 1) && \
      cat minisat_build.log || true
  # 6. Make MiniSat binary globally available (handle alternative output path)
  RUN if [ -f /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      elif [ -f /home/cc/minisat/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      fi
  ENV PATH="/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:${PATH}"
  # 7. Copy project files (expect context provides all source)
  COPY --chown=cc:cc . /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 8. (Optional) Export JAVA_HOME, update PATH in a profile script for interactive sessions
  RUN echo "export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=\$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile
  # 9. Prepare test directory if not present
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC/test
  # 10. Set default shell to bash and working directory
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 11. Diagnostics before Enhanced_Kodkod build
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing for Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && \
      ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== build.sh contents ===" && \
      cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh || true && \
      chmod +x Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh
  # 11a. Output directory listing and contents before build for further debugging
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing inside Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/src ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/src || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/lib ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/lib || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/util ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/util || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ===" && (cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml || true)
  # 11b. Check for required files before build, then attempt to build Enhanced_Kodkod, always output build log for debugging
  RUN if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh ]; then \
        echo "build.sh missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ]; then \
        echo "build.xml missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -d Enhanced_Kodkod/src ]; then \
        echo "src directory missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      cd Enhanced_Kodkod && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1; \
      status=$?; \
      echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
      tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
      cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
      if [ $status -ne 0 ]; then \
        echo '=== Enhanced_Kodkod build failed! ==='; \
        exit $status; \
      fi
  # 12. Build Enumerator_Estimator (keep after Enhanced_Kodkod success)
  RUN cd Enumerator_Estimator && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1 || ( \
        echo '=== Enumerator_Estimator build failed! ==='; \
        echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
        tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
        cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
        exit 1)
  RUN cat Enumerator_Estimator/build_sh_output.log || true
  # 13. Entrypoint: open shell by default
  ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 11 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  # 1. Install system dependencies: OpenJDK 8, Ant, CMake, GCC, Git, Python3 (optional), build-essential, wget, unzip, libz-dev
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        openjdk-8-jdk \
        ant \
        cmake \
        build-essential \
        git \
        python3 \
        wget \
        unzip \
        ca-certificates \
        libz-dev \
        g++ \
        make && \
      apt-get clean && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # 2. Set JAVA_HOME and update PATH for Java and Ant
  ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
  ENV PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:$PATH"
  # 3. Create user and working directories
  RUN useradd -ms /bin/bash cc
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  RUN chown -R cc:cc /home/cc
  USER cc
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 4. Clone SymMC repository (replace <SymMC-repo-url> with actual repo URL)
  # ARG SYMMC_REPO_URL
  # RUN git clone $SYMMC_REPO_URL /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # Instead, expect ADD/COPY of code at build time
  # 5. Clone and build MiniSat with diagnostics and build log output for debugging.
  RUN git clone https://github.com/niklasso/minisat.git /home/cc/minisat && \
      cd /home/cc/minisat && \
      git submodule update --init --recursive || true && \
      ls -l && \
      (cat README.md || true) && \
      make clean || true && \
      make -j$(nproc) > minisat_build.log 2>&1 || ( \
          echo "MiniSat build failed. Directory listing:"; ls -l; \
          echo "Makefile contents:"; cat Makefile || true; \
          echo "README.md:"; cat README.md || true; \
          echo "Last 50 lines of minisat_build.log:"; tail -n 50 minisat_build.log || true; \
          cat minisat_build.log || true; \
          exit 1) && \
      cat minisat_build.log || true
  # 6. Make MiniSat binary globally available (handle alternative output path)
  RUN if [ -f /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      elif [ -f /home/cc/minisat/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      fi
  ENV PATH="/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:${PATH}"
  # 7. Copy project files (expect context provides all source)
  COPY --chown=cc:cc . /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 8. (Optional) Export JAVA_HOME, update PATH in a profile script for interactive sessions
  RUN echo "export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=\$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile
  # 9. Prepare test directory if not present
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC/test
  # 10. Set default shell to bash and working directory
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 11. Diagnostics before Enhanced_Kodkod build
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing for Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && \
      ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== build.sh contents ===" && \
      cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh || true && \
      chmod +x Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh
  # 11a. Output directory listing and contents before build for further debugging
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing inside Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/src ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/src || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/lib ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/lib || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/util ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/util || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ===" && (cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml || true)
  # 11b. Check for required files before build, then attempt to build Enhanced_Kodkod, always output build log for debugging
  RUN if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh ]; then \
        echo "build.sh missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ]; then \
        echo "build.xml missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -d Enhanced_Kodkod/src ]; then \
        echo "src directory missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      cd Enhanced_Kodkod && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1; \
      status=$?; \
      echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
      tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
      cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
      if [ $status -ne 0 ]; then \
        echo '=== Enhanced_Kodkod build failed! ==='; \
        exit $status; \
      fi
  # 12. Build Enumerator_Estimator (keep after Enhanced_Kodkod success)
  RUN cd Enumerator_Estimator && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1 || ( \
        echo '=== Enumerator_Estimator build failed! ==='; \
        echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
        tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
        cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
        exit 1)
  RUN cat Enumerator_Estimator/build_sh_output.log || true
  # 13. Entrypoint: open shell by default
  ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 12 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  # 1. Install system dependencies: OpenJDK 8, Ant, CMake, GCC, Git, Python3 (optional), build-essential, wget, unzip, libz-dev
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        openjdk-8-jdk \
        ant \
        cmake \
        build-essential \
        git \
        python3 \
        wget \
        unzip \
        ca-certificates \
        libz-dev \
        g++ \
        make && \
      apt-get clean && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # 2. Set JAVA_HOME and update PATH for Java and Ant
  ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
  ENV PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:$PATH"
  # 3. Create user and working directories
  RUN useradd -ms /bin/bash cc
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  RUN chown -R cc:cc /home/cc
  USER cc
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 4. Clone SymMC repository (replace <SymMC-repo-url> with actual repo URL)
  # ARG SYMMC_REPO_URL
  # RUN git clone $SYMMC_REPO_URL /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # Instead, expect ADD/COPY of code at build time
  # 5. Clone and build MiniSat with diagnostics and build log output for debugging.
  RUN git clone https://github.com/niklasso/minisat.git /home/cc/minisat && \
      cd /home/cc/minisat && \
      git submodule update --init --recursive || true && \
      ls -l && \
      (cat README.md || true) && \
      make clean || true && \
      make -j$(nproc) > minisat_build.log 2>&1 || ( \
          echo "MiniSat build failed. Directory listing:"; ls -l; \
          echo "Makefile contents:"; cat Makefile || true; \
          echo "README.md:"; cat README.md || true; \
          echo "Last 50 lines of minisat_build.log:"; tail -n 50 minisat_build.log || true; \
          cat minisat_build.log || true; \
          exit 1) && \
      cat minisat_build.log || true
  # 6. Make MiniSat binary globally available (handle alternative output path)
  RUN if [ -f /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      elif [ -f /home/cc/minisat/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      fi
  ENV PATH="/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:${PATH}"
  # 7. Copy project files (expect context provides all source)
  COPY --chown=cc:cc . /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 8. (Optional) Export JAVA_HOME, update PATH in a profile script for interactive sessions
  RUN echo "export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=\$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile
  # 9. Prepare test directory if not present
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC/test
  # 10. Set default shell to bash and working directory
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 11. Diagnostics before Enhanced_Kodkod build
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing for Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && \
      ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== build.sh contents ===" && \
      cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh || true && \
      chmod +x Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh
  # 11a. Output directory listing and contents before build for further debugging
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing inside Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/src ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/src || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/lib ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/lib || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/util ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/util || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ===" && (cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml || true)
  # 11b. Check for required files before build, then attempt to build Enhanced_Kodkod, always output build log for debugging
  RUN if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh ]; then \
        echo "build.sh missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ]; then \
        echo "build.xml missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -d Enhanced_Kodkod/src ]; then \
        echo "src directory missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      cd Enhanced_Kodkod && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1; \
      status=$?; \
      echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
      tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
      cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
      if [ $status -ne 0 ]; then \
        echo '=== Enhanced_Kodkod build failed! ==='; \
        exit $status; \
      fi
  # 12. Build Enumerator_Estimator (keep after Enhanced_Kodkod success)
  RUN cd Enumerator_Estimator && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1 || ( \
        echo '=== Enumerator_Estimator build failed! ==='; \
        echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
        tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
        cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
        exit 1)
  RUN cat Enumerator_Estimator/build_sh_output.log || true
  # 13. Entrypoint: open shell by default
  ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 13 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  # 1. Install system dependencies: OpenJDK 8, Ant, CMake, GCC, Git, Python3 (optional), build-essential, wget, unzip, libz-dev
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        openjdk-8-jdk \
        ant \
        cmake \
        build-essential \
        git \
        python3 \
        wget \
        unzip \
        ca-certificates \
        libz-dev \
        g++ \
        make && \
      apt-get clean && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # 2. Set JAVA_HOME and update PATH for Java and Ant
  ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
  ENV PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:$PATH"
  # 3. Create user and working directories
  RUN useradd -ms /bin/bash cc
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  RUN chown -R cc:cc /home/cc
  USER cc
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 4. Clone SymMC repository (replace <SymMC-repo-url> with actual repo URL)
  # ARG SYMMC_REPO_URL
  # RUN git clone $SYMMC_REPO_URL /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # Instead, expect ADD/COPY of code at build time
  # 5. Clone and build MiniSat with diagnostics and build log output for debugging.
  RUN git clone https://github.com/niklasso/minisat.git /home/cc/minisat && \
      cd /home/cc/minisat && \
      git submodule update --init --recursive || true && \
      ls -l && \
      (cat README.md || true) && \
      make clean || true && \
      make -j$(nproc) > minisat_build.log 2>&1 || ( \
          echo "MiniSat build failed. Directory listing:"; ls -l; \
          echo "Makefile contents:"; cat Makefile || true; \
          echo "README.md:"; cat README.md || true; \
          echo "Last 50 lines of minisat_build.log:"; tail -n 50 minisat_build.log || true; \
          cat minisat_build.log || true; \
          exit 1) && \
      cat minisat_build.log || true
  # 6. Make MiniSat binary globally available (handle alternative output path)
  RUN if [ -f /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      elif [ -f /home/cc/minisat/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      fi
  ENV PATH="/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:${PATH}"
  # 7. Copy project files (expect context provides all source)
  COPY --chown=cc:cc . /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 8. (Optional) Export JAVA_HOME, update PATH in a profile script for interactive sessions
  RUN echo "export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=\$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile
  # 9. Prepare test directory if not present
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC/test
  # 10. Set default shell to bash and working directory
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 11. Diagnostics before Enhanced_Kodkod build
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing for Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && \
      ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== build.sh contents ===" && \
      cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh || true && \
      chmod +x Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh
  # 11a. Output directory listing and contents before build for further debugging
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing inside Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/src ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/src || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/lib ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/lib || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/util ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/util || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ===" && (cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml || true)
  # 11b. Check for required files before build, then attempt to build Enhanced_Kodkod, always output build log for debugging
  RUN if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh ]; then \
        echo "build.sh missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ]; then \
        echo "build.xml missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -d Enhanced_Kodkod/src ]; then \
        echo "src directory missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      cd Enhanced_Kodkod && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1; \
      status=$?; \
      echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
      tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
      cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
      if [ $status -ne 0 ]; then \
        echo '=== Enhanced_Kodkod build failed! ==='; \
        exit $status; \
      fi
  # 12. Build Enumerator_Estimator (keep after Enhanced_Kodkod success)
  RUN cd Enumerator_Estimator && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1 || ( \
        echo '=== Enumerator_Estimator build failed! ==='; \
        echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
        tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
        cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
        exit 1)
  RUN cat Enumerator_Estimator/build_sh_output.log || true
  # 13. Entrypoint: open shell by default
  ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 14 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  # 1. Install system dependencies: OpenJDK 8, Ant, CMake, GCC, Git, Python3 (optional), build-essential, wget, unzip, libz-dev
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        openjdk-8-jdk \
        ant \
        cmake \
        build-essential \
        git \
        python3 \
        wget \
        unzip \
        ca-certificates \
        libz-dev \
        g++ \
        make && \
      apt-get clean && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # 2. Set JAVA_HOME and update PATH for Java and Ant
  ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
  ENV PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:$PATH"
  # 3. Create user and working directories
  RUN useradd -ms /bin/bash cc
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  RUN chown -R cc:cc /home/cc
  USER cc
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 4. Clone SymMC repository (replace <SymMC-repo-url> with actual repo URL)
  # ARG SYMMC_REPO_URL
  # RUN git clone $SYMMC_REPO_URL /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # Instead, expect ADD/COPY of code at build time
  # 5. Clone and build MiniSat with diagnostics and build log output for debugging.
  RUN git clone https://github.com/niklasso/minisat.git /home/cc/minisat && \
      cd /home/cc/minisat && \
      git submodule update --init --recursive || true && \
      ls -l && \
      (cat README.md || true) && \
      make clean || true && \
      make -j$(nproc) > minisat_build.log 2>&1 || ( \
          echo "MiniSat build failed. Directory listing:"; ls -l; \
          echo "Makefile contents:"; cat Makefile || true; \
          echo "README.md:"; cat README.md || true; \
          echo "Last 50 lines of minisat_build.log:"; tail -n 50 minisat_build.log || true; \
          cat minisat_build.log || true; \
          exit 1) && \
      cat minisat_build.log || true
  # 6. Make MiniSat binary globally available (handle alternative output path)
  RUN if [ -f /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      elif [ -f /home/cc/minisat/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      fi
  ENV PATH="/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:${PATH}"
  # 7. Copy project files (expect context provides all source)
  COPY --chown=cc:cc . /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 8. (Optional) Export JAVA_HOME, update PATH in a profile script for interactive sessions
  RUN echo "export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=\$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile
  # 9. Prepare test directory if not present
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC/test
  # 10. Set default shell to bash and working directory
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 11. Diagnostics before Enhanced_Kodkod build
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing for Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && \
      ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== build.sh contents ===" && \
      cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh || true && \
      chmod +x Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh
  # 11a. Output directory listing and contents before build for further debugging
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing inside Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/src ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/src || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/lib ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/lib || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/util ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/util || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ===" && (cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml || true)
  # 11b. Check for required files before build, then attempt to build Enhanced_Kodkod, always output build log for debugging
  RUN if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh ]; then \
        echo "build.sh missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ]; then \
        echo "build.xml missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -d Enhanced_Kodkod/src ]; then \
        echo "src directory missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      cd Enhanced_Kodkod && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1; \
      status=$?; \
      echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
      tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
      cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
      if [ $status -ne 0 ]; then \
        echo '=== Enhanced_Kodkod build failed! ==='; \
        exit $status; \
      fi
  # 12. Build Enumerator_Estimator (keep after Enhanced_Kodkod success)
  RUN cd Enumerator_Estimator && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1 || ( \
        echo '=== Enumerator_Estimator build failed! ==='; \
        echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
        tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
        cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
        exit 1)
  RUN cat Enumerator_Estimator/build_sh_output.log || true
  # 13. Entrypoint: open shell by default
  ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 15 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  # 1. Install system dependencies: OpenJDK 8, Ant, CMake, GCC, Git, Python3 (optional), build-essential, wget, unzip, libz-dev
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        openjdk-8-jdk \
        ant \
        cmake \
        build-essential \
        git \
        python3 \
        wget \
        unzip \
        ca-certificates \
        libz-dev \
        g++ \
        make && \
      apt-get clean && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # 2. Set JAVA_HOME and update PATH for Java and Ant
  ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
  ENV PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:$PATH"
  # 3. Create user and working directories
  RUN useradd -ms /bin/bash cc
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  RUN chown -R cc:cc /home/cc
  USER cc
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 4. Clone SymMC repository (replace <SymMC-repo-url> with actual repo URL)
  # ARG SYMMC_REPO_URL
  # RUN git clone $SYMMC_REPO_URL /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # Instead, expect ADD/COPY of code at build time
  # 5. Clone and build MiniSat with diagnostics and build log output for debugging.
  RUN git clone https://github.com/niklasso/minisat.git /home/cc/minisat && \
      cd /home/cc/minisat && \
      git submodule update --init --recursive || true && \
      ls -l && \
      (cat README.md || true) && \
      make clean || true && \
      make -j$(nproc) > minisat_build.log 2>&1 || ( \
          echo "MiniSat build failed. Directory listing:"; ls -l; \
          echo "Makefile contents:"; cat Makefile || true; \
          echo "README.md:"; cat README.md || true; \
          echo "Last 50 lines of minisat_build.log:"; tail -n 50 minisat_build.log || true; \
          cat minisat_build.log || true; \
          exit 1) && \
      cat minisat_build.log || true
  # 6. Make MiniSat binary globally available (handle alternative output path)
  RUN if [ -f /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      elif [ -f /home/cc/minisat/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      fi
  ENV PATH="/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:${PATH}"
  # 7. Copy project files (expect context provides all source)
  COPY --chown=cc:cc . /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 8. (Optional) Export JAVA_HOME, update PATH in a profile script for interactive sessions
  RUN echo "export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=\$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile
  # 9. Prepare test directory if not present
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC/test
  # 10. Set default shell to bash and working directory
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 11. Diagnostics before Enhanced_Kodkod build
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing for Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && \
      ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== build.sh contents ===" && \
      cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh || true && \
      chmod +x Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh
  # 11a. Output directory listing and contents before build for further debugging
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing inside Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/src ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/src || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/lib ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/lib || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/util ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/util || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ===" && (cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml || true)
  # 11b. Check for required files before build, then attempt to build Enhanced_Kodkod, always output build log for debugging
  RUN if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh ]; then \
        echo "build.sh missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ]; then \
        echo "build.xml missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -d Enhanced_Kodkod/src ]; then \
        echo "src directory missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      cd Enhanced_Kodkod && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1; \
      status=$?; \
      echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
      tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
      cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
      if [ $status -ne 0 ]; then \
        echo '=== Enhanced_Kodkod build failed! ==='; \
        exit $status; \
      fi
  # 12. Build Enumerator_Estimator (keep after Enhanced_Kodkod success)
  RUN cd Enumerator_Estimator && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1 || ( \
        echo '=== Enumerator_Estimator build failed! ==='; \
        echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
        tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
        cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
        exit 1)
  RUN cat Enumerator_Estimator/build_sh_output.log || true
  # 13. Entrypoint: open shell by default
  ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 16 ---
