DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  # 1. Install system dependencies: OpenJDK 8, Ant, CMake, GCC, Git, Python3 (optional), build-essential, wget, unzip, libz-dev
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        openjdk-8-jdk \
        ant \
        cmake \
        build-essential \
        git \
        python3 \
        wget \
        unzip \
        ca-certificates \
        libz-dev \
        g++ \
        make && \
      apt-get clean && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # 2. Set JAVA_HOME and update PATH for Java and Ant
  ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
  ENV PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:$PATH"
  # 3. Create user and working directories
  RUN useradd -ms /bin/bash cc
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  RUN chown -R cc:cc /home/cc
  USER cc
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 4. Clone SymMC repository (replace <SymMC-repo-url> with actual repo URL)
  # ARG SYMMC_REPO_URL
  # RUN git clone $SYMMC_REPO_URL /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # Instead, expect ADD/COPY of code at build time
  # 5. Clone and build MiniSat with diagnostics and build log output for debugging.
  RUN git clone https://github.com/niklasso/minisat.git /home/cc/minisat && \
      cd /home/cc/minisat && \
      git submodule update --init --recursive || true && \
      ls -l && \
      (cat README.md || true) && \
      make clean || true && \
      make -j$(nproc) > minisat_build.log 2>&1 || ( \
          echo "MiniSat build failed. Directory listing:"; ls -l; \
          echo "Makefile contents:"; cat Makefile || true; \
          echo "README.md:"; cat README.md || true; \
          echo "Last 50 lines of minisat_build.log:"; tail -n 50 minisat_build.log || true; \
          cat minisat_build.log || true; \
          exit 1) && \
      cat minisat_build.log || true
  # 6. Make MiniSat binary globally available (handle alternative output path)
  RUN if [ -f /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      elif [ -f /home/cc/minisat/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      fi
  ENV PATH="/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:${PATH}"
  # 7. Copy project files (expect context provides all source)
  COPY --chown=cc:cc . /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 8. (Optional) Export JAVA_HOME, update PATH in a profile script for interactive sessions
  RUN echo "export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=\$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile
  # 9. Prepare test directory if not present
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC/test
  # 10. Set default shell to bash and working directory
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 11. Diagnostics before Enhanced_Kodkod build
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing for Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && \
      ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== build.sh contents ===" && \
      cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh || true && \
      chmod +x Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh
  # 11a. Output directory listing and contents before build for further debugging
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing inside Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/src ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/src || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/lib ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/lib || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/util ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/util || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ===" && (cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml || true)
  # 11b. Check for required files before build, then attempt to build Enhanced_Kodkod, always output build log for debugging
  RUN if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh ]; then \
        echo "build.sh missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ]; then \
        echo "build.xml missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -d Enhanced_Kodkod/src ]; then \
        echo "src directory missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      cd Enhanced_Kodkod && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1; \
      status=$?; \
      echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
      tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
      cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
      if [ $status -ne 0 ]; then \
        echo '=== Enhanced_Kodkod build failed! ==='; \
        exit $status; \
      fi
  # 12. Build Enumerator_Estimator (keep after Enhanced_Kodkod success)
  RUN cd Enumerator_Estimator && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1 || ( \
        echo '=== Enumerator_Estimator build failed! ==='; \
        echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
        tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
        cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
        exit 1)
  RUN cat Enumerator_Estimator/build_sh_output.log || true
  # 13. Entrypoint: open shell by default
  ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 17 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  # 1. Install system dependencies: OpenJDK 8, Ant, CMake, GCC, Git, Python3 (optional), build-essential, wget, unzip, libz-dev
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        openjdk-8-jdk \
        ant \
        cmake \
        build-essential \
        git \
        python3 \
        wget \
        unzip \
        ca-certificates \
        libz-dev \
        g++ \
        make && \
      apt-get clean && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # 2. Set JAVA_HOME and update PATH for Java and Ant
  ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
  ENV PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:$PATH"
  # 3. Create user and working directories
  RUN useradd -ms /bin/bash cc
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  RUN chown -R cc:cc /home/cc
  USER cc
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 4. Clone SymMC repository (replace <SymMC-repo-url> with actual repo URL)
  # ARG SYMMC_REPO_URL
  # RUN git clone $SYMMC_REPO_URL /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # Instead, expect ADD/COPY of code at build time
  # 5. Clone and build MiniSat with diagnostics and build log output for debugging.
  RUN git clone https://github.com/niklasso/minisat.git /home/cc/minisat && \
      cd /home/cc/minisat && \
      git submodule update --init --recursive || true && \
      ls -l && \
      (cat README.md || true) && \
      make clean || true && \
      make -j$(nproc) > minisat_build.log 2>&1 || ( \
          echo "MiniSat build failed. Directory listing:"; ls -l; \
          echo "Makefile contents:"; cat Makefile || true; \
          echo "README.md:"; cat README.md || true; \
          echo "Last 50 lines of minisat_build.log:"; tail -n 50 minisat_build.log || true; \
          cat minisat_build.log || true; \
          exit 1) && \
      cat minisat_build.log || true
  # 6. Make MiniSat binary globally available (handle alternative output path)
  RUN if [ -f /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      elif [ -f /home/cc/minisat/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      fi
  ENV PATH="/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:${PATH}"
  # 7. Copy project files (expect context provides all source)
  COPY --chown=cc:cc . /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 8. (Optional) Export JAVA_HOME, update PATH in a profile script for interactive sessions
  RUN echo "export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=\$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile
  # 9. Prepare test directory if not present
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC/test
  # 10. Set default shell to bash and working directory
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 11. Diagnostics before Enhanced_Kodkod build
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing for Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && \
      ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== build.sh contents ===" && \
      cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh || true && \
      chmod +x Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh
  # 11a. Output directory listing and contents before build for further debugging
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing inside Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/src ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/src || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/lib ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/lib || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/util ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/util || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ===" && (cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml || true)
  # 11b. Check for required files before build, then attempt to build Enhanced_Kodkod, always output build log for debugging
  RUN if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh ]; then \
        echo "build.sh missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ]; then \
        echo "build.xml missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -d Enhanced_Kodkod/src ]; then \
        echo "src directory missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      cd Enhanced_Kodkod && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1; \
      status=$?; \
      echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
      tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
      cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
      if [ $status -ne 0 ]; then \
        echo '=== Enhanced_Kodkod build failed! ==='; \
        exit $status; \
      fi
  # 12. Build Enumerator_Estimator (keep after Enhanced_Kodkod success)
  RUN cd Enumerator_Estimator && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1 || ( \
        echo '=== Enumerator_Estimator build failed! ==='; \
        echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
        tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
        cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
        exit 1)
  RUN cat Enumerator_Estimator/build_sh_output.log || true
  # 13. Entrypoint: open shell by default
  ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 18 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  # 1. Install system dependencies: OpenJDK 8, Ant, CMake, GCC, Git, Python3 (optional), build-essential, wget, unzip, libz-dev
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        openjdk-8-jdk \
        ant \
        cmake \
        build-essential \
        git \
        python3 \
        wget \
        unzip \
        ca-certificates \
        libz-dev \
        g++ \
        make && \
      apt-get clean && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # 2. Set JAVA_HOME and update PATH for Java and Ant
  ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
  ENV PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:$PATH"
  # 3. Create user and working directories
  RUN useradd -ms /bin/bash cc
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  RUN chown -R cc:cc /home/cc
  USER cc
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 4. Clone SymMC repository (replace <SymMC-repo-url> with actual repo URL)
  # ARG SYMMC_REPO_URL
  # RUN git clone $SYMMC_REPO_URL /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # Instead, expect ADD/COPY of code at build time
  # 5. Clone and build MiniSat with diagnostics and build log output for debugging.
  RUN git clone https://github.com/niklasso/minisat.git /home/cc/minisat && \
      cd /home/cc/minisat && \
      git submodule update --init --recursive || true && \
      ls -l && \
      (cat README.md || true) && \
      make clean || true && \
      make -j$(nproc) > minisat_build.log 2>&1 || ( \
          echo "MiniSat build failed. Directory listing:"; ls -l; \
          echo "Makefile contents:"; cat Makefile || true; \
          echo "README.md:"; cat README.md || true; \
          echo "Last 50 lines of minisat_build.log:"; tail -n 50 minisat_build.log || true; \
          cat minisat_build.log || true; \
          exit 1) && \
      cat minisat_build.log || true
  # 6. Make MiniSat binary globally available (handle alternative output path)
  RUN if [ -f /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      elif [ -f /home/cc/minisat/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      fi
  ENV PATH="/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:${PATH}"
  # 7. Copy project files (expect context provides all source)
  COPY --chown=cc:cc . /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 8. (Optional) Export JAVA_HOME, update PATH in a profile script for interactive sessions
  RUN echo "export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=\$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile
  # 9. Prepare test directory if not present
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC/test
  # 10. Set default shell to bash and working directory
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 11. Diagnostics before Enhanced_Kodkod build
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing for Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && \
      ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== build.sh contents ===" && \
      cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh || true && \
      chmod +x Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh
  # 11a. Output directory listing and contents before build for further debugging
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing inside Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/src ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/src || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/lib ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/lib || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/util ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/util || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ===" && (cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml || true)
  # 11b. Check for required files before build, then attempt to build Enhanced_Kodkod, always output build log for debugging
  RUN if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh ]; then \
        echo "build.sh missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ]; then \
        echo "build.xml missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -d Enhanced_Kodkod/src ]; then \
        echo "src directory missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      cd Enhanced_Kodkod && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1; \
      status=$?; \
      echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
      tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
      cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
      if [ $status -ne 0 ]; then \
        echo '=== Enhanced_Kodkod build failed! ==='; \
        exit $status; \
      fi
  # 12. Build Enumerator_Estimator (keep after Enhanced_Kodkod success)
  RUN cd Enumerator_Estimator && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1 || ( \
        echo '=== Enumerator_Estimator build failed! ==='; \
        echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
        tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
        cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
        exit 1)
  RUN cat Enumerator_Estimator/build_sh_output.log || true
  # 13. Entrypoint: open shell by default
  ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 19 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  # 1. Install system dependencies: OpenJDK 8, Ant, CMake, GCC, Git, Python3 (optional), build-essential, wget, unzip, libz-dev
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        openjdk-8-jdk \
        ant \
        cmake \
        build-essential \
        git \
        python3 \
        wget \
        unzip \
        ca-certificates \
        libz-dev \
        g++ \
        make && \
      apt-get clean && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # 2. Set JAVA_HOME and update PATH for Java and Ant
  ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
  ENV PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:$PATH"
  # 3. Create user and working directories
  RUN useradd -ms /bin/bash cc
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  RUN chown -R cc:cc /home/cc
  USER cc
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 4. Clone SymMC repository (replace <SymMC-repo-url> with actual repo URL)
  # ARG SYMMC_REPO_URL
  # RUN git clone $SYMMC_REPO_URL /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # Instead, expect ADD/COPY of code at build time
  # 5. Clone and build MiniSat with diagnostics and build log output for debugging.
  RUN git clone https://github.com/niklasso/minisat.git /home/cc/minisat && \
      cd /home/cc/minisat && \
      git submodule update --init --recursive || true && \
      ls -l && \
      (cat README.md || true) && \
      make clean || true && \
      make -j$(nproc) > minisat_build.log 2>&1 || ( \
          echo "MiniSat build failed. Directory listing:"; ls -l; \
          echo "Makefile contents:"; cat Makefile || true; \
          echo "README.md:"; cat README.md || true; \
          echo "Last 50 lines of minisat_build.log:"; tail -n 50 minisat_build.log || true; \
          cat minisat_build.log || true; \
          exit 1) && \
      cat minisat_build.log || true
  # 6. Make MiniSat binary globally available (handle alternative output path)
  RUN if [ -f /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      elif [ -f /home/cc/minisat/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      fi
  ENV PATH="/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:${PATH}"
  # 7. Copy project files (expect context provides all source)
  COPY --chown=cc:cc . /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 8. (Optional) Export JAVA_HOME, update PATH in a profile script for interactive sessions
  RUN echo "export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=\$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile
  # 9. Prepare test directory if not present
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC/test
  # 10. Set default shell to bash and working directory
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 11. Diagnostics before Enhanced_Kodkod build
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing for Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && \
      ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== build.sh contents ===" && \
      cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh || true && \
      chmod +x Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh
  # 11a. Output directory listing and contents before build for further debugging
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing inside Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/src ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/src || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/lib ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/lib || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/util ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/util || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ===" && (cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml || true)
  # 11b. Check for required files before build, then attempt to build Enhanced_Kodkod, always output build log for debugging
  RUN if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh ]; then \
        echo "build.sh missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ]; then \
        echo "build.xml missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -d Enhanced_Kodkod/src ]; then \
        echo "src directory missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      cd Enhanced_Kodkod && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1; \
      status=$?; \
      echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
      tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
      cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
      if [ $status -ne 0 ]; then \
        echo '=== Enhanced_Kodkod build failed! ==='; \
        exit $status; \
      fi
  # 12. Build Enumerator_Estimator (keep after Enhanced_Kodkod success)
  RUN cd Enumerator_Estimator && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1 || ( \
        echo '=== Enumerator_Estimator build failed! ==='; \
        echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
        tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
        cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
        exit 1)
  RUN cat Enumerator_Estimator/build_sh_output.log || true
  # 13. Entrypoint: open shell by default
  ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 20 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  # 1. Install system dependencies: OpenJDK 8, Ant, CMake, GCC, Git, Python3 (optional), build-essential, wget, unzip, libz-dev
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        openjdk-8-jdk \
        ant \
        cmake \
        build-essential \
        git \
        python3 \
        wget \
        unzip \
        ca-certificates \
        libz-dev \
        g++ \
        make && \
      apt-get clean && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # 2. Set JAVA_HOME and update PATH for Java and Ant
  ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
  ENV PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:$PATH"
  # 3. Create user and working directories
  RUN useradd -ms /bin/bash cc
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  RUN chown -R cc:cc /home/cc
  USER cc
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 5. Clone and build MiniSat with diagnostics and build log output for debugging.
  RUN git clone https://github.com/niklasso/minisat.git /home/cc/minisat && \
      cd /home/cc/minisat && \
      git submodule update --init --recursive || true && \
      ls -l && \
      (cat README.md || true) && \
      make clean || true && \
      make -j$(nproc) > minisat_build.log 2>&1 || ( \
          echo "MiniSat build failed. Directory listing:"; ls -l; \
          echo "Makefile contents:"; cat Makefile || true; \
          echo "README.md:"; cat README.md || true; \
          echo "Last 50 lines of minisat_build.log:"; tail -n 50 minisat_build.log || true; \
          cat minisat_build.log || true; \
          exit 1) && \
      cat minisat_build.log || true
  # 6. Make MiniSat binary globally available (handle alternative output path)
  RUN if [ -f /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      elif [ -f /home/cc/minisat/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      fi
  ENV PATH="/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:${PATH}"
  # 7. Copy project files (expect context provides all source)
  COPY --chown=cc:cc . /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 8. (Optional) Export JAVA_HOME, update PATH in a profile script for interactive sessions
  RUN echo "export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=\$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile
  # 9. Prepare test directory if not present
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC/test
  # 10. Set default shell to bash and working directory
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 11. Diagnostics before Enhanced_Kodkod build
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing for Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && \
      ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== build.sh contents ===" && \
      cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh || true && \
      chmod +x Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh
  # 11a. Output directory listing and contents before build for further debugging
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing inside Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/src ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/src || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/lib ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/lib || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/util ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/util || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ===" && (cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml || true)
  # 11b. Check for required files before build, then attempt to build Enhanced_Kodkod, always output build log for debugging
  RUN if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh ]; then \
        echo "build.sh missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ]; then \
        echo "build.xml missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -d Enhanced_Kodkod/src ]; then \
        echo "src directory missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      cd Enhanced_Kodkod && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1; \
      status=$?; \
      echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
      tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
      cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
      if [ $status -ne 0 ]; then \
        echo '=== Enhanced_Kodkod build failed! ==='; \
        exit $status; \
      fi
  # 12. Build Enumerator_Estimator (keep after Enhanced_Kodkod success)
  RUN cd Enumerator_Estimator && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1 || ( \
        echo '=== Enumerator_Estimator build failed! ==='; \
        echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
        tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
        cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
        exit 1)
  RUN cat Enumerator_Estimator/build_sh_output.log || true
  # 13. Entrypoint: open shell by default
  ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 21 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  # 1. Install system dependencies: OpenJDK 8, Ant, CMake, GCC, Git, Python3 (optional), build-essential, wget, unzip, libz-dev
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        openjdk-8-jdk \
        ant \
        cmake \
        build-essential \
        git \
        python3 \
        wget \
        unzip \
        ca-certificates \
        libz-dev \
        g++ \
        make && \
      apt-get clean && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # 2. Set JAVA_HOME and update PATH for Java and Ant
  ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
  ENV PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:$PATH"
  # 3. Create user and working directories
  RUN useradd -ms /bin/bash cc
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  RUN chown -R cc:cc /home/cc
  USER cc
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 5. Clone and build MiniSat with diagnostics and build log output for debugging.
  RUN git clone https://github.com/niklasso/minisat.git /home/cc/minisat && \
      cd /home/cc/minisat && \
      git submodule update --init --recursive || true && \
      ls -l && \
      (cat README.md || true) && \
      make clean || true && \
      make -j$(nproc) > minisat_build.log 2>&1 || ( \
          echo "MiniSat build failed. Directory listing:"; ls -l; \
          echo "Makefile contents:"; cat Makefile || true; \
          echo "README.md:"; cat README.md || true; \
          echo "Last 50 lines of minisat_build.log:"; tail -n 50 minisat_build.log || true; \
          cat minisat_build.log || true; \
          exit 1) && \
      cat minisat_build.log || true
  # 6. Make MiniSat binary globally available (handle alternative output path)
  RUN if [ -f /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      elif [ -f /home/cc/minisat/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      fi
  ENV PATH="/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:${PATH}"
  # 7. Copy project files (expect context provides all source)
  COPY --chown=cc:cc . /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 8. (Optional) Export JAVA_HOME, update PATH in a profile script for interactive sessions
  RUN echo "export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=\$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile
  # 9. Prepare test directory if not present
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC/test
  # 10. Set default shell to bash and working directory
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 11. Diagnostics before Enhanced_Kodkod build
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing for Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && \
      ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== build.sh contents ===" && \
      cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh || true && \
      chmod +x Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh
  # 11a. Output directory listing and contents before build for further debugging
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing inside Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/src ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/src || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/lib ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/lib || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/util ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/util || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ===" && (cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml || true)
  # 11b. Check for required files before build, then attempt to build Enhanced_Kodkod, always output build log for debugging
  RUN if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh ]; then \
        echo "build.sh missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ]; then \
        echo "build.xml missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -d Enhanced_Kodkod/src ]; then \
        echo "src directory missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      cd Enhanced_Kodkod && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1; \
      status=$?; \
      echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
      tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
      cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
      if [ $status -ne 0 ]; then \
        echo '=== Enhanced_Kodkod build failed! ==='; \
        exit $status; \
      fi
  # 12. Build Enumerator_Estimator (keep after Enhanced_Kodkod success)
  RUN cd Enumerator_Estimator && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1 || ( \
        echo '=== Enumerator_Estimator build failed! ==='; \
        echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
        tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
        cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
        exit 1)
  RUN cat Enumerator_Estimator/build_sh_output.log || true
  # 13. Entrypoint: open shell by default
  ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 22 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  # 1. Install system dependencies: OpenJDK 8, Ant, CMake, GCC, Git, Python3 (optional), build-essential, wget, unzip, libz-dev
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        openjdk-8-jdk \
        ant \
        cmake \
        build-essential \
        git \
        python3 \
        wget \
        unzip \
        ca-certificates \
        libz-dev \
        g++ \
        make && \
      apt-get clean && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # 2. Set JAVA_HOME and update PATH for Java and Ant
  ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
  ENV PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:$PATH"
  # 3. Create user and working directories
  RUN useradd -ms /bin/bash cc
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  RUN chown -R cc:cc /home/cc
  USER cc
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 5. Clone and build MiniSat with diagnostics and build log output for debugging.
  RUN git clone https://github.com/niklasso/minisat.git /home/cc/minisat && \
      cd /home/cc/minisat && \
      git submodule update --init --recursive || true && \
      ls -l && \
      (cat README.md || true) && \
      make clean || true && \
      make -j$(nproc) > minisat_build.log 2>&1 || ( \
          echo "MiniSat build failed. Directory listing:"; ls -l; \
          echo "Makefile contents:"; cat Makefile || true; \
          echo "README.md:"; cat README.md || true; \
          echo "Last 50 lines of minisat_build.log:"; tail -n 50 minisat_build.log || true; \
          cat minisat_build.log || true; \
          exit 1) && \
      cat minisat_build.log || true
  # 6. Make MiniSat binary globally available (handle alternative output path)
  RUN if [ -f /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      elif [ -f /home/cc/minisat/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      fi
  ENV PATH="/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:${PATH}"
  # 7. Copy project files (expect context provides all source)
  COPY --chown=cc:cc . /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 8. (Optional) Export JAVA_HOME, update PATH in a profile script for interactive sessions
  RUN echo "export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=\$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile
  # 9. Prepare test directory if not present
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC/test
  # 10. Set default shell to bash and working directory
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 11. Diagnostics before Enhanced_Kodkod build
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing for Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && \
      ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== build.sh contents ===" && \
      cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh || true && \
      chmod +x Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh
  # 11a. Output directory listing and contents before build for further debugging
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing inside Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/src ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/src || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/lib ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/lib || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/util ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/util || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ===" && (cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml || true)
  # 11b. Check for required files before build, then attempt to build Enhanced_Kodkod, always output build log for debugging
  RUN if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh ]; then \
        echo "build.sh missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ]; then \
        echo "build.xml missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -d Enhanced_Kodkod/src ]; then \
        echo "src directory missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      cd Enhanced_Kodkod && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1; \
      status=$?; \
      echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
      tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
      cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
      if [ $status -ne 0 ]; then \
        echo '=== Enhanced_Kodkod build failed! ==='; \
        exit $status; \
      fi
  # 12. Build Enumerator_Estimator (keep after Enhanced_Kodkod success)
  RUN cd Enumerator_Estimator && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1 || ( \
        echo '=== Enumerator_Estimator build failed! ==='; \
        echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
        tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
        cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
        exit 1)
  RUN cat Enumerator_Estimator/build_sh_output.log || true
  # 13. Entrypoint: open shell by default
  ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 23 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  # 1. Install system dependencies: OpenJDK 8, Ant, CMake, GCC, Git, Python3 (optional), build-essential, wget, unzip, libz-dev
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        openjdk-8-jdk \
        ant \
        cmake \
        build-essential \
        git \
        python3 \
        wget \
        unzip \
        ca-certificates \
        libz-dev \
        g++ \
        make && \
      apt-get clean && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # 2. Set JAVA_HOME and update PATH for Java and Ant
  ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
  ENV PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:$PATH"
  # 3. Create user and working directories
  RUN useradd -ms /bin/bash cc
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  RUN chown -R cc:cc /home/cc
  USER cc
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 5. Clone and build MiniSat with diagnostics and build log output for debugging.
  RUN git clone https://github.com/niklasso/minisat.git /home/cc/minisat && \
      cd /home/cc/minisat && \
      git submodule update --init --recursive || true && \
      ls -l && \
      (cat README.md || true) && \
      make clean || true && \
      make -j$(nproc) > minisat_build.log 2>&1 || ( \
          echo "MiniSat build failed. Directory listing:"; ls -l; \
          echo "Makefile contents:"; cat Makefile || true; \
          echo "README.md:"; cat README.md || true; \
          echo "Last 50 lines of minisat_build.log:"; tail -n 50 minisat_build.log || true; \
          cat minisat_build.log || true; \
          exit 1) && \
      cat minisat_build.log || true
  # 6. Make MiniSat binary globally available (handle alternative output path)
  RUN if [ -f /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      elif [ -f /home/cc/minisat/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      fi
  ENV PATH="/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:${PATH}"
  # 7. Copy project files (expect context provides all source)
  COPY --chown=cc:cc . /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 8. (Optional) Export JAVA_HOME, update PATH in a profile script for interactive sessions
  RUN echo "export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=\$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile
  # 9. Prepare test directory if not present
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC/test
  # 10. Set default shell to bash and working directory
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 11. Diagnostics before Enhanced_Kodkod build
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing for Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && \
      ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== build.sh contents ===" && \
      cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh || true && \
      chmod +x Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh
  # 11a. Output directory listing and contents before build for further debugging
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing inside Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/src ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/src || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/lib ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/lib || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/util ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/util || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ===" && (cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml || true)
  # 11b. Check for required files before build, then attempt to build Enhanced_Kodkod, always output build log for debugging
  RUN if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh ]; then \
        echo "build.sh missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ]; then \
        echo "build.xml missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -d Enhanced_Kodkod/src ]; then \
        echo "src directory missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      cd Enhanced_Kodkod && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1; \
      status=$?; \
      echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
      tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
      cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
      if [ $status -ne 0 ]; then \
        echo '=== Enhanced_Kodkod build failed! ==='; \
        exit $status; \
      fi
  # 12. Build Enumerator_Estimator (keep after Enhanced_Kodkod success)
  RUN cd Enumerator_Estimator && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1 || ( \
        echo '=== Enumerator_Estimator build failed! ==='; \
        echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
        tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
        cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
        exit 1)
  RUN cat Enumerator_Estimator/build_sh_output.log || true
  # 13. Entrypoint: open shell by default
  ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 24 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  # 1. Install system dependencies: OpenJDK 8, Ant, CMake, GCC, Git, Python3 (optional), build-essential, wget, unzip, libz-dev
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        openjdk-8-jdk \
        ant \
        cmake \
        build-essential \
        git \
        python3 \
        wget \
        unzip \
        ca-certificates \
        libz-dev \
        g++ \
        make && \
      apt-get clean && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # 2. Set JAVA_HOME and update PATH for Java and Ant
  ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
  ENV PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:$PATH"
  # 3. Create user and working directories
  RUN useradd -ms /bin/bash cc
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  RUN chown -R cc:cc /home/cc
  USER cc
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 5. Clone and build MiniSat with diagnostics and build log output for debugging.
  RUN git clone https://github.com/niklasso/minisat.git /home/cc/minisat && \
      cd /home/cc/minisat && \
      git submodule update --init --recursive || true && \
      ls -l && \
      (cat README.md || true) && \
      make clean || true && \
      make -j$(nproc) > minisat_build.log 2>&1 || ( \
          echo "MiniSat build failed. Directory listing:"; ls -l; \
          echo "Makefile contents:"; cat Makefile || true; \
          echo "README.md:"; cat README.md || true; \
          echo "Last 50 lines of minisat_build.log:"; tail -n 50 minisat_build.log || true; \
          cat minisat_build.log || true; \
          exit 1) && \
      cat minisat_build.log || true
  # 6. Make MiniSat binary globally available (handle alternative output path)
  RUN if [ -f /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      elif [ -f /home/cc/minisat/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      fi
  ENV PATH="/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:${PATH}"
  # 7. Copy project files (expect context provides all source)
  COPY --chown=cc:cc . /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 8. (Optional) Export JAVA_HOME, update PATH in a profile script for interactive sessions
  RUN echo "export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=\$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile
  # 9. Prepare test directory if not present
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC/test
  # 10. Set default shell to bash and working directory
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 11. Diagnostics before Enhanced_Kodkod build
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing for Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && \
      ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== build.sh contents ===" && \
      cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh || true && \
      chmod +x Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh
  # 11a. Output directory listing and contents before build for further debugging
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing inside Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/src ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/src || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/lib ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/lib || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/util ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/util || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ===" && (cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml || true)
  # 11b. Check for required files before build, then attempt to build Enhanced_Kodkod, always output build log for debugging
  RUN if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh ]; then \
        echo "build.sh missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ]; then \
        echo "build.xml missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -d Enhanced_Kodkod/src ]; then \
        echo "src directory missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      cd Enhanced_Kodkod && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1; \
      status=$?; \
      echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
      tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
      cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
      if [ $status -ne 0 ]; then \
        echo '=== Enhanced_Kodkod build failed! ==='; \
        exit $status; \
      fi
  # 12. Build Enumerator_Estimator (keep after Enhanced_Kodkod success)
  RUN cd Enumerator_Estimator && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1 || ( \
        echo '=== Enumerator_Estimator build failed! ==='; \
        echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
        tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
        cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
        exit 1)
  RUN cat Enumerator_Estimator/build_sh_output.log || true
  # 13. Entrypoint: open shell by default
  ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 25 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  # 1. Install system dependencies: OpenJDK 8, Ant, CMake, GCC, Git, Python3 (optional), build-essential, wget, unzip, libz-dev
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        openjdk-8-jdk \
        ant \
        cmake \
        build-essential \
        git \
        python3 \
        wget \
        unzip \
        ca-certificates \
        libz-dev \
        g++ \
        make && \
      apt-get clean && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # 2. Set JAVA_HOME and update PATH for Java and Ant
  ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
  ENV PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:$PATH"
  # 3. Create user and working directories
  RUN useradd -ms /bin/bash cc
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  RUN chown -R cc:cc /home/cc
  USER cc
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 5. Clone and build MiniSat with diagnostics and build log output for debugging.
  RUN git clone https://github.com/niklasso/minisat.git /home/cc/minisat && \
      cd /home/cc/minisat && \
      git submodule update --init --recursive || true && \
      ls -l && \
      (cat README.md || true) && \
      make clean || true && \
      make -j$(nproc) > minisat_build.log 2>&1 || ( \
          echo "MiniSat build failed. Directory listing:"; ls -l; \
          echo "Makefile contents:"; cat Makefile || true; \
          echo "README.md:"; cat README.md || true; \
          echo "Last 50 lines of minisat_build.log:"; tail -n 50 minisat_build.log || true; \
          cat minisat_build.log || true; \
          exit 1) && \
      cat minisat_build.log || true
  # 6. Make MiniSat binary globally available (handle alternative output path)
  RUN if [ -f /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      elif [ -f /home/cc/minisat/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      fi
  ENV PATH="/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:${PATH}"
  # 7. Copy project files (expect context provides all source)
  COPY --chown=cc:cc . /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 8. (Optional) Export JAVA_HOME, update PATH in a profile script for interactive sessions
  RUN echo "export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=\$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile
  # 9. Prepare test directory if not present
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC/test
  # 10. Set default shell to bash and working directory
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 11. Diagnostics before Enhanced_Kodkod build
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing for Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && \
      ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== build.sh contents ===" && \
      cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh || true && \
      chmod +x Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh
  # 11a. Output directory listing and contents before build for further debugging
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing inside Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/src ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/src || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/lib ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/lib || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/util ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/util || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ===" && (cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml || true)
  # 11b. Check for required files before build, then attempt to build Enhanced_Kodkod, always output build log for debugging
  RUN if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh ]; then \
        echo "build.sh missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ]; then \
        echo "build.xml missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -d Enhanced_Kodkod/src ]; then \
        echo "src directory missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      cd Enhanced_Kodkod && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1; \
      status=$?; \
      echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
      tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
      cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
      if [ $status -ne 0 ]; then \
        echo '=== Enhanced_Kodkod build failed! ==='; \
        exit $status; \
      fi
  # 12. Build Enumerator_Estimator (keep after Enhanced_Kodkod success)
  RUN cd Enumerator_Estimator && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1 || ( \
        echo '=== Enumerator_Estimator build failed! ==='; \
        echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
        tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
        cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
        exit 1)
  RUN cat Enumerator_Estimator/build_sh_output.log || true
  # 13. Entrypoint: open shell by default
  ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 26 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  # 1. Install system dependencies: OpenJDK 8, Ant, CMake, GCC, Git, Python3 (optional), build-essential, wget, unzip, libz-dev
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        openjdk-8-jdk \
        ant \
        cmake \
        build-essential \
        git \
        python3 \
        wget \
        unzip \
        ca-certificates \
        libz-dev \
        g++ \
        make && \
      apt-get clean && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # 2. Set JAVA_HOME and update PATH for Java and Ant
  ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
  ENV PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:$PATH"
  # 3. Create user and working directories
  RUN useradd -ms /bin/bash cc
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  RUN chown -R cc:cc /home/cc
  USER cc
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 5. Clone and build MiniSat with diagnostics and build log output for debugging.
  RUN git clone https://github.com/niklasso/minisat.git /home/cc/minisat && \
      cd /home/cc/minisat && \
      git submodule update --init --recursive || true && \
      ls -l && \
      (cat README.md || true) && \
      make clean || true && \
      make -j$(nproc) > minisat_build.log 2>&1 || ( \
          echo "MiniSat build failed. Directory listing:"; ls -l; \
          echo "Makefile contents:"; cat Makefile || true; \
          echo "README.md:"; cat README.md || true; \
          echo "Last 50 lines of minisat_build.log:"; tail -n 50 minisat_build.log || true; \
          cat minisat_build.log || true; \
          exit 1) && \
      cat minisat_build.log || true
  # 6. Make MiniSat binary globally available (handle alternative output path)
  RUN if [ -f /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      elif [ -f /home/cc/minisat/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      fi
  ENV PATH="/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:${PATH}"
  # 7. Copy project files (expect context provides all source)
  COPY --chown=cc:cc . /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 8. (Optional) Export JAVA_HOME, update PATH in a profile script for interactive sessions
  RUN echo "export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=\$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile
  # 9. Prepare test directory if not present
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC/test
  # 10. Set default shell to bash and working directory
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 11. Diagnostics before Enhanced_Kodkod build
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing for Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && \
      ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== build.sh contents ===" && \
      cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh || true && \
      chmod +x Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh
  # 11a. Output directory listing and contents before build for further debugging
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing inside Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/src ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/src || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/lib ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/lib || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/util ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/util || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ===" && (cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml || true)
  # 11b. Check for required files before build, then attempt to build Enhanced_Kodkod, always output build log for debugging
  RUN if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh ]; then \
        echo "build.sh missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ]; then \
        echo "build.xml missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -d Enhanced_Kodkod/src ]; then \
        echo "src directory missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      cd Enhanced_Kodkod && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1; \
      status=$?; \
      echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
      tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
      cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
      if [ $status -ne 0 ]; then \
        echo '=== Enhanced_Kodkod build failed! ==='; \
        exit $status; \
      fi
  # 12. Build Enumerator_Estimator (keep after Enhanced_Kodkod success)
  RUN cd Enumerator_Estimator && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1 || ( \
        echo '=== Enumerator_Estimator build failed! ==='; \
        echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
        tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
        cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
        exit 1)
  RUN cat Enumerator_Estimator/build_sh_output.log || true
  # 13. Entrypoint: open shell by default
  ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 27 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  # 1. Install system dependencies: OpenJDK 8, Ant, CMake, GCC, Git, Python3 (optional), build-essential, wget, unzip, libz-dev
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        openjdk-8-jdk \
        ant \
        cmake \
        build-essential \
        git \
        python3 \
        wget \
        unzip \
        ca-certificates \
        libz-dev \
        g++ \
        make && \
      apt-get clean && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # 2. Set JAVA_HOME and update PATH for Java and Ant
  ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
  ENV PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:$PATH"
  # 3. Create user and working directories
  RUN useradd -ms /bin/bash cc
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  RUN chown -R cc:cc /home/cc
  USER cc
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 5. Clone and build MiniSat with diagnostics and build log output for debugging.
  RUN git clone https://github.com/niklasso/minisat.git /home/cc/minisat && \
      cd /home/cc/minisat && \
      git submodule update --init --recursive || true && \
      ls -l && \
      (cat README.md || true) && \
      make clean || true && \
      make -j$(nproc) > minisat_build.log 2>&1 || ( \
          echo "MiniSat build failed. Directory listing:"; ls -l; \
          echo "Makefile contents:"; cat Makefile || true; \
          echo "README.md:"; cat README.md || true; \
          echo "Last 50 lines of minisat_build.log:"; tail -n 50 minisat_build.log || true; \
          cat minisat_build.log || true; \
          exit 1) && \
      cat minisat_build.log || true
  # 6. Make MiniSat binary globally available (handle alternative output path)
  RUN if [ -f /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      elif [ -f /home/cc/minisat/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      fi
  ENV PATH="/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:${PATH}"
  # 7. Copy project files (expect context provides all source)
  COPY --chown=cc:cc . /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 8. (Optional) Export JAVA_HOME, update PATH in a profile script for interactive sessions
  RUN echo "export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=\$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile
  # 9. Prepare test directory if not present
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC/test
  # 10. Set default shell to bash and working directory
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 11. Diagnostics before Enhanced_Kodkod build
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing for Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && \
      ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== build.sh contents ===" && \
      cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh || true && \
      chmod +x Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh
  # 11a. Output directory listing and contents before build for further debugging
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing inside Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/src ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/src || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/lib ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/lib || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/util ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/util || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ===" && (cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml || true)
  # 11b. Check for required files before build, then attempt to build Enhanced_Kodkod, always output build log for debugging
  RUN if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh ]; then \
        echo "build.sh missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ]; then \
        echo "build.xml missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -d Enhanced_Kodkod/src ]; then \
        echo "src directory missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      cd Enhanced_Kodkod && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1; \
      status=$?; \
      echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
      tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
      cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
      if [ $status -ne 0 ]; then \
        echo '=== Enhanced_Kodkod build failed! ==='; \
        exit $status; \
      fi
  # 12. Build Enumerator_Estimator (keep after Enhanced_Kodkod success)
  RUN cd Enumerator_Estimator && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1 || ( \
        echo '=== Enumerator_Estimator build failed! ==='; \
        echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
        tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
        cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
        exit 1)
  RUN cat Enumerator_Estimator/build_sh_output.log || true
  # 13. Entrypoint: open shell by default
  ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 28 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  # 1. Install system dependencies: OpenJDK 8, Ant, CMake, GCC, Git, Python3 (optional), build-essential, wget, unzip, libz-dev
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        openjdk-8-jdk \
        ant \
        cmake \
        build-essential \
        git \
        python3 \
        wget \
        unzip \
        ca-certificates \
        libz-dev \
        g++ \
        make && \
      apt-get clean && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # 2. Set JAVA_HOME and update PATH for Java and Ant
  ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
  ENV PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:$PATH"
  # 3. Create user and working directories
  RUN useradd -ms /bin/bash cc
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  RUN chown -R cc:cc /home/cc
  USER cc
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 5. Clone and build MiniSat with diagnostics and build log output for debugging.
  RUN git clone https://github.com/niklasso/minisat.git /home/cc/minisat && \
      cd /home/cc/minisat && \
      git submodule update --init --recursive || true && \
      ls -l && \
      (cat README.md || true) && \
      make clean || true && \
      make -j$(nproc) > minisat_build.log 2>&1 || ( \
          echo "MiniSat build failed. Directory listing:"; ls -l; \
          echo "Makefile contents:"; cat Makefile || true; \
          echo "README.md:"; cat README.md || true; \
          echo "Last 50 lines of minisat_build.log:"; tail -n 50 minisat_build.log || true; \
          cat minisat_build.log || true; \
          exit 1) && \
      cat minisat_build.log || true
  # 6. Make MiniSat binary globally available (handle alternative output path)
  RUN if [ -f /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      elif [ -f /home/cc/minisat/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      fi
  ENV PATH="/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:${PATH}"
  # 7. Copy project files (expect context provides all source)
  COPY --chown=cc:cc . /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 8. (Optional) Export JAVA_HOME, update PATH in a profile script for interactive sessions
  RUN echo "export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=\$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile
  # 9. Prepare test directory if not present
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC/test
  # 10. Set default shell to bash and working directory
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 11. Diagnostics before Enhanced_Kodkod build
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing for Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && \
      ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== build.sh contents ===" && \
      cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh || true && \
      chmod +x Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh
  # 11a. Output directory listing and contents before build for further debugging
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing inside Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/src ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/src || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/lib ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/lib || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/util ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/util || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ===" && (cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml || true)
  # 11b. Check for required files before build, then attempt to build Enhanced_Kodkod, always output build log for debugging
  RUN if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh ]; then \
        echo "build.sh missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ]; then \
        echo "build.xml missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -d Enhanced_Kodkod/src ]; then \
        echo "src directory missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      echo "All required files present in Enhanced_Kodkod." && \
      cd Enhanced_Kodkod && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1; \
      status=$?; \
      echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
      tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
      cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
      if [ $status -ne 0 ]; then \
        echo '=== Enhanced_Kodkod build failed! ==='; \
        exit $status; \
      fi
  # 12. Build Enumerator_Estimator (keep after Enhanced_Kodkod success)
  RUN cd Enumerator_Estimator && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1 || ( \
        echo '=== Enumerator_Estimator build failed! ==='; \
        echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
        tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
        cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
        exit 1)
  RUN cat Enumerator_Estimator/build_sh_output.log || true
  # 13. Entrypoint: open shell by default
  ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 29 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  # 1. Install system dependencies: OpenJDK 8, Ant, CMake, GCC, Git, Python3 (optional), build-essential, wget, unzip, libz-dev
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        openjdk-8-jdk \
        ant \
        cmake \
        build-essential \
        git \
        python3 \
        wget \
        unzip \
        ca-certificates \
        libz-dev \
        g++ \
        make && \
      apt-get clean && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # 2. Set JAVA_HOME and update PATH for Java and Ant
  ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
  ENV PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:$PATH"
  # 3. Create user and working directories
  RUN useradd -ms /bin/bash cc
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  RUN chown -R cc:cc /home/cc
  USER cc
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 5. Clone and build MiniSat with diagnostics and build log output for debugging.
  RUN git clone https://github.com/niklasso/minisat.git /home/cc/minisat && \
      cd /home/cc/minisat && \
      git submodule update --init --recursive || true && \
      ls -l && \
      (cat README.md || true) && \
      make clean || true && \
      make -j$(nproc) > minisat_build.log 2>&1 || ( \
          echo "MiniSat build failed. Directory listing:"; ls -l; \
          echo "Makefile contents:"; cat Makefile || true; \
          echo "README.md:"; cat README.md || true; \
          echo "Last 50 lines of minisat_build.log:"; tail -n 50 minisat_build.log || true; \
          cat minisat_build.log || true; \
          exit 1) && \
      cat minisat_build.log || true
  # 6. Make MiniSat binary globally available (handle alternative output path)
  RUN if [ -f /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      elif [ -f /home/cc/minisat/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      fi
  ENV PATH="/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:${PATH}"
  # 7. Copy project files (expect context provides all source)
  COPY --chown=cc:cc . /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 8. (Optional) Export JAVA_HOME, update PATH in a profile script for interactive sessions
  RUN echo "export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=\$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile
  # 9. Prepare test directory if not present
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC/test
  # 10. Set default shell to bash and working directory
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 11. Diagnostics before Enhanced_Kodkod build
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing for Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && \
      ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== build.sh contents ===" && \
      cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh || true && \
      chmod +x Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh
  # 11a. Output directory listing and contents before build for further debugging
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing inside Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/src ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/src || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/lib ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/lib || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/util ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/util || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ===" && (cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml || true)
  # 11b. Check for required files before build, then attempt to build Enhanced_Kodkod, always output build log for debugging
  RUN if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh ]; then \
        echo "build.sh missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ]; then \
        echo "build.xml missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -d Enhanced_Kodkod/src ]; then \
        echo "src directory missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      echo "All required files present in Enhanced_Kodkod." && \
      cd Enhanced_Kodkod && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1; \
      status=$?; \
      echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
      tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
      cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
      if [ $status -ne 0 ]; then \
        echo '=== Enhanced_Kodkod build failed! ==='; \
        exit $status; \
      fi
  # 12. Build Enumerator_Estimator (keep after Enhanced_Kodkod success)
  RUN cd Enumerator_Estimator && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1 || ( \
        echo '=== Enumerator_Estimator build failed! ==='; \
        echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
        tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
        cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
        exit 1)
  RUN cat Enumerator_Estimator/build_sh_output.log || true
  # 13. Entrypoint: open shell by default
  ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 30 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:22.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  # 1. Install system dependencies: OpenJDK 8, Ant, CMake, GCC, Git, Python3 (optional), build-essential, wget, unzip, libz-dev
  RUN apt-get update && \
      apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        openjdk-8-jdk \
        ant \
        cmake \
        build-essential \
        git \
        python3 \
        wget \
        unzip \
        ca-certificates \
        libz-dev \
        g++ \
        make && \
      apt-get clean && \
      rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # 2. Set JAVA_HOME and update PATH for Java and Ant
  ENV JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
  ENV PATH="$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:$PATH"
  # 3. Create user and working directories
  RUN useradd -ms /bin/bash cc
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  RUN chown -R cc:cc /home/cc
  USER cc
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 5. Clone and build MiniSat with diagnostics and build log output for debugging.
  RUN git clone https://github.com/niklasso/minisat.git /home/cc/minisat && \
      cd /home/cc/minisat && \
      git submodule update --init --recursive || true && \
      ls -l && \
      (cat README.md || true) && \
      make clean || true && \
      make -j$(nproc) > minisat_build.log 2>&1 || ( \
          echo "MiniSat build failed. Directory listing:"; ls -l; \
          echo "Makefile contents:"; cat Makefile || true; \
          echo "README.md:"; cat README.md || true; \
          echo "Last 50 lines of minisat_build.log:"; tail -n 50 minisat_build.log || true; \
          cat minisat_build.log || true; \
          exit 1) && \
      cat minisat_build.log || true
  # 6. Make MiniSat binary globally available (handle alternative output path)
  RUN if [ -f /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      elif [ -f /home/cc/minisat/minisat ]; then \
        ln -sf /home/cc/minisat/minisat /home/cc/minisat/minisat-bin; \
      fi
  ENV PATH="/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:${PATH}"
  # 7. Copy project files (expect context provides all source)
  COPY --chown=cc:cc . /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 8. (Optional) Export JAVA_HOME, update PATH in a profile script for interactive sessions
  RUN echo "export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=\$JAVA_HOME/bin:/usr/bin/ant:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile && \
      echo "export PATH=/home/cc/minisat/build/release/bin:/home/cc/minisat:\$PATH" >> /home/cc/.profile
  # 9. Prepare test directory if not present
  RUN mkdir -p /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC/test
  # 10. Set default shell to bash and working directory
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data/SymMC
  # 11. Diagnostics before Enhanced_Kodkod build
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing for Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && \
      ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== build.sh contents ===" && \
      cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh || true && \
      chmod +x Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh
  # 11a. Output directory listing and contents before build for further debugging
  RUN echo "=== Directory listing inside Enhanced_Kodkod ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/src ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/src || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/lib ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/lib || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/util ===" && ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod/util || true && \
      echo "=== Listing of Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ===" && (cat Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml || true)
  # 11b. Check for required files before build, then attempt to build Enhanced_Kodkod, always output build log for debugging
  RUN if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.sh ]; then \
        echo "build.sh missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -f Enhanced_Kodkod/build.xml ]; then \
        echo "build.xml missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      if [ ! -d Enhanced_Kodkod/src ]; then \
        echo "src directory missing in Enhanced_Kodkod!"; \
        ls -l Enhanced_Kodkod || true; \
        exit 1; \
      fi && \
      echo "All required files present in Enhanced_Kodkod." && \
      cd Enhanced_Kodkod && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1; \
      status=$?; \
      echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
      tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
      cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
      if [ $status -ne 0 ]; then \
        echo '=== Enhanced_Kodkod build failed! ==='; \
        exit $status; \
      fi
  # 12. Build Enumerator_Estimator (keep after Enhanced_Kodkod success)
  RUN cd Enumerator_Estimator && ./build.sh > build_sh_output.log 2>&1 || ( \
        echo '=== Enumerator_Estimator build failed! ==='; \
        echo '=== Last 50 lines of build_sh_output.log ==='; \
        tail -n 50 build_sh_output.log || true; \
        cat build_sh_output.log || true; \
        exit 1)
  RUN cat Enumerator_Estimator/build_sh_output.log || true
  # 13. Entrypoint: open shell by default
  ENTRYPOINT ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 31 ---
